<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_1/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "This Regulation lays down rules relating to the protection of natural persons with regard to the processing of personal data and rules relating to the free movement of personal data."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 1, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 1 (Subject-matter and objectives), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_1>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_1> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_1/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "This Regulation protects fundamental rights and freedoms of natural persons and in particular their right to the protection of personal data."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 1, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 1 (Subject-matter and objectives), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_1>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_1> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_1/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The free movement of personal data within the Union shall be neither restricted nor prohibited for reasons connected with the protection of natural persons with regard to the processing of personal data."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 1, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 1 (Subject-matter and objectives), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_1>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_1> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_2/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "This Regulation applies to the processing of personal data wholly or partly by automated means and to the processing other than by automated means of personal data which form part of a filing system or are intended to form part of a filing system."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 2, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 2 (Material scope), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_2>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_2> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_2/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "This Regulation does not apply to the processing of personal data:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 2, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 2 (Material scope), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_2>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_2> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_2/Point_2a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "in the course of an activity which falls outside the scope of Union law;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 2, point 2a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 2 (Material scope), point 2a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_2>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_2> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_2/Point_2b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "by the Member States when carrying out activities which fall within the scope of Chapter 2 of Title V of the TEU;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 2, point 2b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 2 (Material scope), point 2b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_2>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_2> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_2/Point_2c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "by a natural person in the course of a purely personal or household activity;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 2, point 2c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 2 (Material scope), point 2c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_2>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_2> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_2/Point_2d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "by competent authorities for the purposes of the prevention, investigation, detection or prosecution of criminal offences or the execution of criminal penalties, including the safeguarding against and the prevention of threats to public security."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 2, point 2d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 2 (Material scope), point 2d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_2>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_2> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_2/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "For the processing of personal data by the Union institutions, bodies, offices and agencies, Regulation (EC) No 45/2001 applies. Regulation (EC) No 45/2001 and other Union legal acts applicable to such processing of personal data shall be adapted to the principles and rules of this Regulation in accordance with Article 98."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 2, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 2 (Material scope), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_2>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_2> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_2/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "This Regulation shall be without prejudice to the application of Directive 2000/31/EC, in particular of the liability rules of intermediary service providers in Articles 12 to 15 of that Directive."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 2, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 2 (Material scope), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_2>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_2> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_3/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "This Regulation applies to the processing of personal data in the context of the activities of an establishment of a controller or a processor in the Union, regardless of whether the processing takes place in the Union or not."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 3, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 3 (Territorial scope), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_3>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_3> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_3/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "This Regulation applies to the processing of personal data of data subjects who are in the Union by a controller or processor not established in the Union, where the processing activities are related to:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 3, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 3 (Territorial scope), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_3>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_3> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_3/Point_2a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the offering of goods or services, irrespective of whether a payment of the data subject is required, to such data subjects in the Union; or"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 3, point 2a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 3 (Territorial scope), point 2a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_3>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_3> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_3/Point_2b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the monitoring of their behaviour as far as their behaviour takes place within the Union."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 3, point 2b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 3 (Territorial scope), point 2b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_3>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_3> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_3/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "This Regulation applies to the processing of personal data by a controller not established in the Union, but in a place where Member State law applies by virtue of public international law."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 3, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 3 (Territorial scope), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_3>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_3> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_text_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "For the purposes of this Regulation:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point text_1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point text_1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘personal data’ means any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person (‘data subject’); an identifiable natural person is one who can be identified, directly or indirectly, in particular by reference to an identifier such as a name, an identification number, location data, an online identifier or to one or more factors specific to the physical, physiological, genetic, mental, economic, cultural or social identity of that natural person;"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘processing’ means any operation or set of operations which is performed on personal data or on sets of personal data, whether or not by automated means, such as collection, recording, organisation, structuring, storage, adaptation or alteration, retrieval, consultation, use, disclosure by transmission, dissemination or otherwise making available, alignment or combination, restriction, erasure or destruction;"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘restriction of processing’ means the marking of stored personal data with the aim of limiting their processing in the future;"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘profiling’ means any form of automated processing of personal data consisting of the use of personal data to evaluate certain personal aspects relating to a natural person, in particular to analyse or predict aspects concerning that natural person's performance at work, economic situation, health, personal preferences, interests, reliability, behaviour, location or movements;"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘pseudonymisation’ means the processing of personal data in such a manner that the personal data can no longer be attributed to a specific data subject without the use of additional information, provided that such additional information is kept separately and is subject to technical and organisational measures to ensure that the personal data are not attributed to an identified or identifiable natural person;"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘filing system’ means any structured set of personal data which are accessible according to specific criteria, whether centralised, decentralised or dispersed on a functional or geographical basis;"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_7>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘controller’ means the natural or legal person, public authority, agency or other body which, alone or jointly with others, determines the purposes and means of the processing of personal data; where the purposes and means of such processing are determined by Union or Member State law, the controller or the specific criteria for its nomination may be provided for by Union or Member State law;"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 7"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 7"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_8>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘processor’ means a natural or legal person, public authority, agency or other body which processes personal data on behalf of the controller;"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 8"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 8"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_9>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘recipient’ means a natural or legal person, public authority, agency or another body, to which the personal data are disclosed, whether a third party or not. However, public authorities which may receive personal data in the framework of a particular inquiry in accordance with Union or Member State law shall not be regarded as recipients; the processing of those data by those public authorities shall be in compliance with the applicable data protection rules according to the purposes of the processing;"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 9"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 9"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_10>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘third party’ means a natural or legal person, public authority, agency or body other than the data subject, controller, processor and persons who, under the direct authority of the controller or processor, are authorised to process personal data;"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 10"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 10"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_11>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘consent’ of the data subject means any freely given, specific, informed and unambiguous indication of the data subject's wishes by which he or she, by a statement or by a clear affirmative action, signifies agreement to the processing of personal data relating to him or her;"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 11"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 11"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_12>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘personal data breach’ means a breach of security leading to the accidental or unlawful destruction, loss, alteration, unauthorised disclosure of, or access to, personal data transmitted, stored or otherwise processed;"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 12"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 12"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_13>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘genetic data’ means personal data relating to the inherited or acquired genetic characteristics of a natural person which give unique information about the physiology or the health of that natural person and which result, in particular, from an analysis of a biological sample from the natural person in question;"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 13"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 13"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_14>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘biometric data’ means personal data resulting from specific technical processing relating to the physical, physiological or behavioural characteristics of a natural person, which allow or confirm the unique identification of that natural person, such as facial images or dactyloscopic data;"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 14"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 14"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_15>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘data concerning health’ means personal data related to the physical or mental health of a natural person, including the provision of health care services, which reveal information about his or her health status;"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 15"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 15"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_16>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘main establishment’ means:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 16"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 16"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_16a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "as regards a controller with establishments in more than one Member State, the place of its central administration in the Union, unless the decisions on the purposes and means of the processing of personal data are taken in another establishment of the controller in the Union and the latter establishment has the power to have such decisions implemented, in which case the establishment having taken such decisions is to be considered to be the main establishment;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 16a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 16a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_16b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "as regards a processor with establishments in more than one Member State, the place of its central administration in the Union, or, if the processor has no central administration in the Union, the establishment of the processor in the Union where the main processing activities in the context of the activities of an establishment of the processor take place to the extent that the processor is subject to specific obligations under this Regulation;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 16b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 16b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_17>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘representative’ means a natural or legal person established in the Union who, designated by the controller or processor in writing pursuant to Article 27, represents the controller or processor with regard to their respective obligations under this Regulation;"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 17"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 17"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_18>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘enterprise’ means a natural or legal person engaged in an economic activity, irrespective of its legal form, including partnerships or associations regularly engaged in an economic activity;"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 18"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 18"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_19>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘group of undertakings’ means a controlling undertaking and its controlled undertakings;"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 19"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 19"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_20>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘binding corporate rules’ means personal data protection policies which are adhered to by a controller or processor established on the territory of a Member State for transfers or a set of transfers of personal data to a controller or processor in one or more third countries within a group of undertakings, or group of enterprises engaged in a joint economic activity;"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 20"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 20"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_21>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘supervisory authority’ means an independent public authority which is established by a Member State pursuant to Article 51;"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 21"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 21"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_22>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘supervisory authority concerned’ means a supervisory authority which is concerned by the processing of personal data because:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 22"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 22"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_22a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the controller or processor is established on the territory of the Member State of that supervisory authority;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 22a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 22a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_22b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "data subjects residing in the Member State of that supervisory authority are substantially affected or likely to be substantially affected by the processing; or"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 22b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 22b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_22c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "a complaint has been lodged with that supervisory authority;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 22c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 22c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_23>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘cross-border processing’ means either:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 23"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 23"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_23a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "processing of personal data which takes place in the context of the activities of establishments in more than one Member State of a controller or processor in the Union where the controller or processor is established in more than one Member State; or"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 23a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 23a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_23b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "processing of personal data which takes place in the context of the activities of a single establishment of a controller or processor in the Union but which substantially affects or is likely to substantially affect data subjects in more than one Member State."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 23b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 23b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_24>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘relevant and reasoned objection’ means an objection to a draft decision as to whether there is an infringement of this Regulation, or whether envisaged action in relation to the controller or processor complies with this Regulation, which clearly demonstrates the significance of the risks posed by the draft decision as regards the fundamental rights and freedoms of data subjects and, where applicable, the free flow of personal data within the Union;"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 24"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 24"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_25>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘information society service’ means a service as defined in point (b) of Article 1(1) of Directive (EU) 2015/1535 of the European Parliament and of the Council (19);"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 25"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 25"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4/Point_26>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "‘international organisation’ means an organisation and its subordinate bodies governed by public international law, or any other body which is set up by, or on the basis of, an agreement between two or more countries."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter I, article 4, point 26"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter I (General provisions), article 4 (Definitions), point 26"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_I/Article_4>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_i_article_4> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_5/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Personal data shall be:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 5, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 5 (Principles relating to processing of personal data), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_5>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_5> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_5/Point_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "processed lawfully, fairly and in a transparent manner in relation to the data subject (‘lawfulness, fairness and transparency’);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 5, point 1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 5 (Principles relating to processing of personal data), point 1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_5>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_5> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_5/Point_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "collected for specified, explicit and legitimate purposes and not further processed in a manner that is incompatible with those purposes; further processing for archiving purposes in the public interest, scientific or historical research purposes or statistical purposes shall, in accordance with Article 89(1), not be considered to be incompatible with the initial purposes (‘purpose limitation’);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 5, point 1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 5 (Principles relating to processing of personal data), point 1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_5>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_5> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_5/Point_1c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "adequate, relevant and limited to what is necessary in relation to the purposes for which they are processed (‘data minimisation’);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 5, point 1c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 5 (Principles relating to processing of personal data), point 1c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_5>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_5> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_5/Point_1d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "accurate and, where necessary, kept up to date; every reasonable step must be taken to ensure that personal data that are inaccurate, having regard to the purposes for which they are processed, are erased or rectified without delay (‘accuracy’);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 5, point 1d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 5 (Principles relating to processing of personal data), point 1d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_5>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_5> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_5/Point_1e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "kept in a form which permits identification of data subjects for no longer than is necessary for the purposes for which the personal data are processed; personal data may be stored for longer periods insofar as the personal data will be processed solely for archiving purposes in the public interest, scientific or historical research purposes or statistical purposes in accordance with Article 89(1) subject to implementation of the appropriate technical and organisational measures required by this Regulation in order to safeguard the rights and freedoms of the data subject (‘storage limitation’);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 5, point 1e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 5 (Principles relating to processing of personal data), point 1e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_5>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_5> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_5/Point_1f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "processed in a manner that ensures appropriate security of the personal data, including protection against unauthorised or unlawful processing and against accidental loss, destruction or damage, using appropriate technical or organisational measures (‘integrity and confidentiality’)."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 5, point 1f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 5 (Principles relating to processing of personal data), point 1f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_5>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_5> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_5/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The controller shall be responsible for, and be able to demonstrate compliance with, paragraph 1 (‘accountability’)."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 5, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 5 (Principles relating to processing of personal data), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_5>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_5> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Processing shall be lawful only if and to the extent that at least one of the following applies:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 6, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 6 (Lawfulness of processing), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_6> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6/Point_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the data subject has given consent to the processing of his or her personal data for one or more specific purposes;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 6, point 1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 6 (Lawfulness of processing), point 1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_6> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6/Point_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "processing is necessary for the performance of a contract to which the data subject is party or in order to take steps at the request of the data subject prior to entering into a contract;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 6, point 1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 6 (Lawfulness of processing), point 1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_6> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6/Point_1c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "processing is necessary for compliance with a legal obligation to which the controller is subject;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 6, point 1c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 6 (Lawfulness of processing), point 1c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_6> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6/Point_1d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "processing is necessary in order to protect the vital interests of the data subject or of another natural person;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 6, point 1d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 6 (Lawfulness of processing), point 1d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_6> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6/Point_1e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "processing is necessary for the performance of a task carried out in the public interest or in the exercise of official authority vested in the controller;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 6, point 1e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 6 (Lawfulness of processing), point 1e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_6> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6/Point_1f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "processing is necessary for the purposes of the legitimate interests pursued by the controller or by a third party, except where such interests are overridden by the interests or fundamental rights and freedoms of the data subject which require protection of personal data, in particular where the data subject is a child."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 6, point 1f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 6 (Lawfulness of processing), point 1f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_6> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6/Point_text_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Point (f) of the first subparagraph shall not apply to processing carried out by public authorities in the performance of their tasks."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 6, point text_2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 6 (Lawfulness of processing), point text_2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_6> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Member States may maintain or introduce more specific provisions to adapt the application of the rules of this Regulation with regard to processing for compliance with points (c) and (e) of paragraph 1 by determining more precisely specific requirements for the processing and other measures to ensure lawful and fair processing including for other specific processing situations as provided for in Chapter IX."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 6, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 6 (Lawfulness of processing), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_6> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The basis for the processing referred to in point (c) and (e) of paragraph 1 shall be laid down by:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 6, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 6 (Lawfulness of processing), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_6> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6/Point_3a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "Union law; or"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 6, point 3a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 6 (Lawfulness of processing), point 3a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_6> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6/Point_3b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "Member State law to which the controller is subject."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 6, point 3b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 6 (Lawfulness of processing), point 3b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_6> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6/Point_text_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The purpose of the processing shall be determined in that legal basis or, as regards the processing referred to in point (e) of paragraph 1, shall be necessary for the performance of a task carried out in the public interest or in the exercise of official authority vested in the controller. That legal basis may contain specific provisions to adapt the application of rules of this Regulation, inter alia: the general conditions governing the lawfulness of processing by the controller; the types of data which are subject to the processing; the data subjects concerned; the entities to, and the purposes for which, the personal data may be disclosed; the purpose limitation; storage periods; and processing operations and processing procedures, including measures to ensure lawful and fair processing such as those for other specific processing situations as provided for in Chapter IX. The Union or the Member State law shall meet an objective of public interest and be proportionate to the legitimate aim pursued."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 6, point text_5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 6 (Lawfulness of processing), point text_5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_6> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where the processing for a purpose other than that for which the personal data have been collected is not based on the data subject's consent or on a Union or Member State law which constitutes a necessary and proportionate measure in a democratic society to safeguard the objectives referred to in Article 23(1), the controller shall, in order to ascertain whether processing for another purpose is compatible with the purpose for which the personal data are initially collected, take into account, inter alia:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 6, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 6 (Lawfulness of processing), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_6> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6/Point_4a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "any link between the purposes for which the personal data have been collected and the purposes of the intended further processing;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 6, point 4a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 6 (Lawfulness of processing), point 4a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_6> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6/Point_4b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the context in which the personal data have been collected, in particular regarding the relationship between data subjects and the controller;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 6, point 4b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 6 (Lawfulness of processing), point 4b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_6> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6/Point_4c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the nature of the personal data, in particular whether special categories of personal data are processed, pursuant to Article 9, or whether personal data related to criminal convictions and offences are processed, pursuant to Article 10;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 6, point 4c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 6 (Lawfulness of processing), point 4c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_6> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6/Point_4d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the possible consequences of the intended further processing for data subjects;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 6, point 4d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 6 (Lawfulness of processing), point 4d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_6> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6/Point_4e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the existence of appropriate safeguards, which may include encryption or pseudonymisation."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 6, point 4e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 6 (Lawfulness of processing), point 4e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_6>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_6> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_7/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where processing is based on consent, the controller shall be able to demonstrate that the data subject has consented to processing of his or her personal data."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 7, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 7 (Conditions for consent), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_7>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_7> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_7/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "If the data subject's consent is given in the context of a written declaration which also concerns other matters, the request for consent shall be presented in a manner which is clearly distinguishable from the other matters, in an intelligible and easily accessible form, using clear and plain language. Any part of such a declaration which constitutes an infringement of this Regulation shall not be binding."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 7, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 7 (Conditions for consent), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_7>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_7> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_7/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The data subject shall have the right to withdraw his or her consent at any time. The withdrawal of consent shall not affect the lawfulness of processing based on consent before its withdrawal. Prior to giving consent, the data subject shall be informed thereof. It shall be as easy to withdraw as to give consent."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 7, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 7 (Conditions for consent), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_7>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_7> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_7/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "When assessing whether consent is freely given, utmost account shall be taken of whether, inter alia, the performance of a contract, including the provision of a service, is conditional on consent to the processing of personal data that is not necessary for the performance of that contract."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 7, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 7 (Conditions for consent), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_7>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_7> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_8/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where point (a) of Article 6(1) applies, in relation to the offer of information society services directly to a child, the processing of the personal data of a child shall be lawful where the child is at least 16 years old. Where the child is below the age of 16 years, such processing shall be lawful only if and to the extent that consent is given or authorised by the holder of parental responsibility over the child."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 8, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 8 (Conditions applicable to child's consent in relation to information society services), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_8>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_8> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_8/Point_text_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Member States may provide by law for a lower age for those purposes provided that such lower age is not below 13 years."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 8, point text_2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 8 (Conditions applicable to child's consent in relation to information society services), point text_2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_8>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_8> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_8/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The controller shall make reasonable efforts to verify in such cases that consent is given or authorised by the holder of parental responsibility over the child, taking into consideration available technology."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 8, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 8 (Conditions applicable to child's consent in relation to information society services), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_8>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_8> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_8/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Paragraph 1 shall not affect the general contract law of Member States such as the rules on the validity, formation or effect of a contract in relation to a child."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 8, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 8 (Conditions applicable to child's consent in relation to information society services), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_8>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_8> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Processing of personal data revealing racial or ethnic origin, political opinions, religious or philosophical beliefs, or trade union membership, and the processing of genetic data, biometric data for the purpose of uniquely identifying a natural person, data concerning health or data concerning a natural person's sex life or sexual orientation shall be prohibited."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 9, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 9 (Processing of special categories of personal data), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_9> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Paragraph 1 shall not apply if one of the following applies:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 9, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 9 (Processing of special categories of personal data), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_9> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9/Point_2a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the data subject has given explicit consent to the processing of those personal data for one or more specified purposes, except where Union or Member State law provide that the prohibition referred to in paragraph 1 may not be lifted by the data subject;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 9, point 2a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 9 (Processing of special categories of personal data), point 2a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_9> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9/Point_2b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "processing is necessary for the purposes of carrying out the obligations and exercising specific rights of the controller or of the data subject in the field of employment and social security and social protection law in so far as it is authorised by Union or Member State law or a collective agreement pursuant to Member State law providing for appropriate safeguards for the fundamental rights and the interests of the data subject;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 9, point 2b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 9 (Processing of special categories of personal data), point 2b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_9> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9/Point_2c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "processing is necessary to protect the vital interests of the data subject or of another natural person where the data subject is physically or legally incapable of giving consent;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 9, point 2c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 9 (Processing of special categories of personal data), point 2c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_9> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9/Point_2d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "processing is carried out in the course of its legitimate activities with appropriate safeguards by a foundation, association or any other not-for-profit body with a political, philosophical, religious or trade union aim and on condition that the processing relates solely to the members or to former members of the body or to persons who have regular contact with it in connection with its purposes and that the personal data are not disclosed outside that body without the consent of the data subjects;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 9, point 2d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 9 (Processing of special categories of personal data), point 2d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_9> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9/Point_2e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "processing relates to personal data which are manifestly made public by the data subject;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 9, point 2e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 9 (Processing of special categories of personal data), point 2e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_9> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9/Point_2f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "processing is necessary for the establishment, exercise or defence of legal claims or whenever courts are acting in their judicial capacity;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 9, point 2f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 9 (Processing of special categories of personal data), point 2f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_9> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9/Point_2g>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "processing is necessary for reasons of substantial public interest, on the basis of Union or Member State law which shall be proportionate to the aim pursued, respect the essence of the right to data protection and provide for suitable and specific measures to safeguard the fundamental rights and the interests of the data subject;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 9, point 2g"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 9 (Processing of special categories of personal data), point 2g"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_9> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9/Point_2h>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "processing is necessary for the purposes of preventive or occupational medicine, for the assessment of the working capacity of the employee, medical diagnosis, the provision of health or social care or treatment or the management of health or social care systems and services on the basis of Union or Member State law or pursuant to contract with a health professional and subject to the conditions and safeguards referred to in paragraph 3;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 9, point 2h"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 9 (Processing of special categories of personal data), point 2h"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_9> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9/Point_2i>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "processing is necessary for reasons of public interest in the area of public health, such as protecting against serious cross-border threats to health or ensuring high standards of quality and safety of health care and of medicinal products or medical devices, on the basis of Union or Member State law which provides for suitable and specific measures to safeguard the rights and freedoms of the data subject, in particular professional secrecy;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 9, point 2i"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 9 (Processing of special categories of personal data), point 2i"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_9> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9/Point_2j>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "processing is necessary for archiving purposes in the public interest, scientific or historical research purposes or statistical purposes in accordance with Article 89(1) based on Union or Member State law which shall be proportionate to the aim pursued, respect the essence of the right to data protection and provide for suitable and specific measures to safeguard the fundamental rights and the interests of the data subject."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 9, point 2j"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 9 (Processing of special categories of personal data), point 2j"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_9> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Personal data referred to in paragraph 1 may be processed for the purposes referred to in point (h) of paragraph 2 when those data are processed by or under the responsibility of a professional subject to the obligation of professional secrecy under Union or Member State law or rules established by national competent bodies or by another person also subject to an obligation of secrecy under Union or Member State law or rules established by national competent bodies."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 9, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 9 (Processing of special categories of personal data), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_9> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Member States may maintain or introduce further conditions, including limitations, with regard to the processing of genetic data, biometric data or data concerning health."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 9, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 9 (Processing of special categories of personal data), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_9>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_9> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_10/Point_text_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Processing of personal data relating to criminal convictions and offences or related security measures based on Article 6(1) shall be carried out only under the control of official authority or when the processing is authorised by Union or Member State law providing for appropriate safeguards for the rights and freedoms of data subjects. Any comprehensive register of criminal convictions shall be kept only under the control of official authority."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 10, point text_1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 10 (Processing of personal data relating to criminal convictions and offences), point text_1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_10>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_10> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_11/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "If the purposes for which a controller processes personal data do not or do no longer require the identification of a data subject by the controller, the controller shall not be obliged to maintain, acquire or process additional information in order to identify the data subject for the sole purpose of complying with this Regulation."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 11, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 11 (Processing which does not require identification), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_11>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_11> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_11/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where, in cases referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article, the controller is able to demonstrate that it is not in a position to identify the data subject, the controller shall inform the data subject accordingly, if possible. In such cases, Articles 15 to 20 shall not apply except where the data subject, for the purpose of exercising his or her rights under those articles, provides additional information enabling his or her identification."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter II, article 11, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter II (Principles), article 11 (Processing which does not require identification), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_II/Article_11>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ii_article_11> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_12/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The controller shall take appropriate measures to provide any information referred to in Articles 13 and 14 and any communication under Articles 15 to 22 and 34 relating to processing to the data subject in a concise, transparent, intelligible and easily accessible form, using clear and plain language, in particular for any information addressed specifically to a child. The information shall be provided in writing, or by other means, including, where appropriate, by electronic means. When requested by the data subject, the information may be provided orally, provided that the identity of the data subject is proven by other means."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 12, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 12 (Transparent information, communication and modalities for the exercise of the rights of the data subject), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_12>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_12> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_12/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The controller shall facilitate the exercise of data subject rights under Articles 15 to 22. In the cases referred to in Article 11(2), the controller shall not refuse to act on the request of the data subject for exercising his or her rights under Articles 15 to 22, unless the controller demonstrates that it is not in a position to identify the data subject."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 12, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 12 (Transparent information, communication and modalities for the exercise of the rights of the data subject), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_12>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_12> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_12/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The controller shall provide information on action taken on a request under Articles 15 to 22 to the data subject without undue delay and in any event within one month of receipt of the request. That period may be extended by two further months where necessary, taking into account the complexity and number of the requests. The controller shall inform the data subject of any such extension within one month of receipt of the request, together with the reasons for the delay. Where the data subject makes the request by electronic form means, the information shall be provided by electronic means where possible, unless otherwise requested by the data subject."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 12, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 12 (Transparent information, communication and modalities for the exercise of the rights of the data subject), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_12>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_12> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_12/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "If the controller does not take action on the request of the data subject, the controller shall inform the data subject without delay and at the latest within one month of receipt of the request of the reasons for not taking action and on the possibility of lodging a complaint with a supervisory authority and seeking a judicial remedy."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 12, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 12 (Transparent information, communication and modalities for the exercise of the rights of the data subject), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_12>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_12> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_12/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Information provided under Articles 13 and 14 and any communication and any actions taken under Articles 15 to 22 and 34 shall be provided free of charge. Where requests from a data subject are manifestly unfounded or excessive, in particular because of their repetitive character, the controller may either:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 12, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 12 (Transparent information, communication and modalities for the exercise of the rights of the data subject), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_12>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_12> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_12/Point_5a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "charge a reasonable fee taking into account the administrative costs of providing the information or communication or taking the action requested; or"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 12, point 5a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 12 (Transparent information, communication and modalities for the exercise of the rights of the data subject), point 5a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_12>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_12> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_12/Point_5b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "refuse to act on the request."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 12, point 5b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 12 (Transparent information, communication and modalities for the exercise of the rights of the data subject), point 5b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_12>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_12> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_12/Point_text_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The controller shall bear the burden of demonstrating the manifestly unfounded or excessive character of the request."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 12, point text_6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 12 (Transparent information, communication and modalities for the exercise of the rights of the data subject), point text_6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_12>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_12> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_12/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Without prejudice to Article 11, where the controller has reasonable doubts concerning the identity of the natural person making the request referred to in Articles 15 to 21, the controller may request the provision of additional information necessary to confirm the identity of the data subject."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 12, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 12 (Transparent information, communication and modalities for the exercise of the rights of the data subject), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_12>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_12> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_12/Point_7>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The information to be provided to data subjects pursuant to Articles 13 and 14 may be provided in combination with standardised icons in order to give in an easily visible, intelligible and clearly legible manner a meaningful overview of the intended processing. Where the icons are presented electronically they shall be machine-readable."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 12, point 7"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 12 (Transparent information, communication and modalities for the exercise of the rights of the data subject), point 7"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_12>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_12> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_12/Point_8>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Commission shall be empowered to adopt delegated acts in accordance with Article 92 for the purpose of determining the information to be presented by the icons and the procedures for providing standardised icons."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 12, point 8"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 12 (Transparent information, communication and modalities for the exercise of the rights of the data subject), point 8"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_12>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_12> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_13/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where personal data relating to a data subject are collected from the data subject, the controller shall, at the time when personal data are obtained, provide the data subject with all of the following information:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 13, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 13 (Information to be provided where personal data are collected from the data subject), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_13>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_13> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_13/Point_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the identity and the contact details of the controller and, where applicable, of the controller's representative;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 13, point 1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 13 (Information to be provided where personal data are collected from the data subject), point 1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_13>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_13> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_13/Point_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the contact details of the data protection officer, where applicable;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 13, point 1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 13 (Information to be provided where personal data are collected from the data subject), point 1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_13>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_13> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_13/Point_1c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the purposes of the processing for which the personal data are intended as well as the legal basis for the processing;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 13, point 1c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 13 (Information to be provided where personal data are collected from the data subject), point 1c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_13>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_13> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_13/Point_1d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "where the processing is based on point (f) of Article 6(1), the legitimate interests pursued by the controller or by a third party;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 13, point 1d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 13 (Information to be provided where personal data are collected from the data subject), point 1d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_13>;  
