                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_14>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_14> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_14/Point_3c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "if a disclosure to another recipient is envisaged, at the latest when the personal data are first disclosed."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 14, point 3c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 14 (Information to be provided where personal data have not been obtained from the data subject), point 3c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_14>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_14> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_14/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where the controller intends to further process the personal data for a purpose other than that for which the personal data were obtained, the controller shall provide the data subject prior to that further processing with information on that other purpose and with any relevant further information as referred to in paragraph 2."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 14, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 14 (Information to be provided where personal data have not been obtained from the data subject), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_14>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_14> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_14/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Paragraphs 1 to 4 shall not apply where and insofar as:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 14, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 14 (Information to be provided where personal data have not been obtained from the data subject), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_14>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_14> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_14/Point_5a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the data subject already has the information;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 14, point 5a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 14 (Information to be provided where personal data have not been obtained from the data subject), point 5a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_14>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_14> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_14/Point_5b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the provision of such information proves impossible or would involve a disproportionate effort, in particular for processing for archiving purposes in the public interest, scientific or historical research purposes or statistical purposes, subject to the conditions and safeguards referred to in Article 89(1) or in so far as the obligation referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article is likely to render impossible or seriously impair the achievement of the objectives of that processing. In such cases the controller shall take appropriate measures to protect the data subject's rights and freedoms and legitimate interests, including making the information publicly available;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 14, point 5b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 14 (Information to be provided where personal data have not been obtained from the data subject), point 5b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_14>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_14> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_14/Point_5c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "obtaining or disclosure is expressly laid down by Union or Member State law to which the controller is subject and which provides appropriate measures to protect the data subject's legitimate interests; or"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 14, point 5c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 14 (Information to be provided where personal data have not been obtained from the data subject), point 5c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_14>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_14> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_14/Point_5d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "where the personal data must remain confidential subject to an obligation of professional secrecy regulated by Union or Member State law, including a statutory obligation of secrecy."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 14, point 5d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 14 (Information to be provided where personal data have not been obtained from the data subject), point 5d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_14>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_14> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The data subject shall have the right to obtain from the controller confirmation as to whether or not personal data concerning him or her are being processed, and, where that is the case, access to the personal data and the following information:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 15, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 15 (Right of access by the data subject), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_15> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15/Point_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the purposes of the processing;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 15, point 1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 15 (Right of access by the data subject), point 1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_15> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15/Point_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the categories of personal data concerned;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 15, point 1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 15 (Right of access by the data subject), point 1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_15> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15/Point_1c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the recipients or categories of recipient to whom the personal data have been or will be disclosed, in particular recipients in third countries or international organisations;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 15, point 1c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 15 (Right of access by the data subject), point 1c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_15> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15/Point_1d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "where possible, the envisaged period for which the personal data will be stored, or, if not possible, the criteria used to determine that period;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 15, point 1d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 15 (Right of access by the data subject), point 1d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_15> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15/Point_1e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the existence of the right to request from the controller rectification or erasure of personal data or restriction of processing of personal data concerning the data subject or to object to such processing;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 15, point 1e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 15 (Right of access by the data subject), point 1e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_15> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15/Point_1f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 15, point 1f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 15 (Right of access by the data subject), point 1f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_15> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15/Point_1g>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "where the personal data are not collected from the data subject, any available information as to their source;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 15, point 1g"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 15 (Right of access by the data subject), point 1g"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_15> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15/Point_1h>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the existence of automated decision-making, including profiling, referred to in Article 22(1) and (4) and, at least in those cases, meaningful information about the logic involved, as well as the significance and the envisaged consequences of such processing for the data subject."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 15, point 1h"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 15 (Right of access by the data subject), point 1h"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_15> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where personal data are transferred to a third country or to an international organisation, the data subject shall have the right to be informed of the appropriate safeguards pursuant to Article 46 relating to the transfer."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 15, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 15 (Right of access by the data subject), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_15> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The controller shall provide a copy of the personal data undergoing processing. For any further copies requested by the data subject, the controller may charge a reasonable fee based on administrative costs. Where the data subject makes the request by electronic means, and unless otherwise requested by the data subject, the information shall be provided in a commonly used electronic form."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 15, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 15 (Right of access by the data subject), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_15> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The right to obtain a copy referred to in paragraph 3 shall not adversely affect the rights and freedoms of others."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 15, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 15 (Right of access by the data subject), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_15>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_15> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_16/Point_text_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The data subject shall have the right to obtain from the controller without undue delay the rectification of inaccurate personal data concerning him or her. Taking into account the purposes of the processing, the data subject shall have the right to have incomplete personal data completed, including by means of providing a supplementary statement."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 16, point text_1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 16 (Right to rectification), point text_1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_16>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_16> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The data subject shall have the right to obtain from the controller the erasure of personal data concerning him or her without undue delay and the controller shall have the obligation to erase personal data without undue delay where one of the following grounds applies:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 17, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 17 (Right to erasure (‘right to be forgotten’)), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_17> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17/Point_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the personal data are no longer necessary in relation to the purposes for which they were collected or otherwise processed;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 17, point 1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 17 (Right to erasure (‘right to be forgotten’)), point 1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_17> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17/Point_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the data subject withdraws consent on which the processing is based according to point (a) of Article 6(1), or point (a) of Article 9(2), and where there is no other legal ground for the processing;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 17, point 1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 17 (Right to erasure (‘right to be forgotten’)), point 1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_17> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17/Point_1c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the data subject objects to the processing pursuant to Article 21(1) and there are no overriding legitimate grounds for the processing, or the data subject objects to the processing pursuant to Article 21(2);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 17, point 1c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 17 (Right to erasure (‘right to be forgotten’)), point 1c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_17> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17/Point_1d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the personal data have been unlawfully processed;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 17, point 1d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 17 (Right to erasure (‘right to be forgotten’)), point 1d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_17> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17/Point_1e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the personal data have to be erased for compliance with a legal obligation in Union or Member State law to which the controller is subject;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 17, point 1e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 17 (Right to erasure (‘right to be forgotten’)), point 1e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_17> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17/Point_1f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the personal data have been collected in relation to the offer of information society services referred to in Article 8(1)."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 17, point 1f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 17 (Right to erasure (‘right to be forgotten’)), point 1f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_17> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where the controller has made the personal data public and is obliged pursuant to paragraph 1 to erase the personal data, the controller, taking account of available technology and the cost of implementation, shall take reasonable steps, including technical measures, to inform controllers which are processing the personal data that the data subject has requested the erasure by such controllers of any links to, or copy or replication of, those personal data."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 17, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 17 (Right to erasure (‘right to be forgotten’)), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_17> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Paragraphs 1 and 2 shall not apply to the extent that processing is necessary:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 17, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 17 (Right to erasure (‘right to be forgotten’)), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_17> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17/Point_3a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "for exercising the right of freedom of expression and information;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 17, point 3a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 17 (Right to erasure (‘right to be forgotten’)), point 3a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_17> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17/Point_3b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "for compliance with a legal obligation which requires processing by Union or Member State law to which the controller is subject or for the performance of a task carried out in the public interest or in the exercise of official authority vested in the controller;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 17, point 3b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 17 (Right to erasure (‘right to be forgotten’)), point 3b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_17> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17/Point_3c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "for reasons of public interest in the area of public health in accordance with points (h) and (i) of Article 9(2) as well as Article 9(3);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 17, point 3c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 17 (Right to erasure (‘right to be forgotten’)), point 3c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_17> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17/Point_3d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "for archiving purposes in the public interest, scientific or historical research purposes or statistical purposes in accordance with Article 89(1) in so far as the right referred to in paragraph 1 is likely to render impossible or seriously impair the achievement of the objectives of that processing; or"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 17, point 3d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 17 (Right to erasure (‘right to be forgotten’)), point 3d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_17> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17/Point_3e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "for the establishment, exercise or defence of legal claims."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 17, point 3e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 17 (Right to erasure (‘right to be forgotten’)), point 3e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_17>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_17> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_18/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The data subject shall have the right to obtain from the controller restriction of processing where one of the following applies:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 18, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 18 (Right to restriction of processing), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_18>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_18> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_18/Point_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the accuracy of the personal data is contested by the data subject, for a period enabling the controller to verify the accuracy of the personal data;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 18, point 1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 18 (Right to restriction of processing), point 1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_18>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_18> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_18/Point_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the processing is unlawful and the data subject opposes the erasure of the personal data and requests the restriction of their use instead;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 18, point 1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 18 (Right to restriction of processing), point 1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_18>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_18> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_18/Point_1c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the controller no longer needs the personal data for the purposes of the processing, but they are required by the data subject for the establishment, exercise or defence of legal claims;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 18, point 1c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 18 (Right to restriction of processing), point 1c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_18>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_18> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_18/Point_1d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the data subject has objected to processing pursuant to Article 21(1) pending the verification whether the legitimate grounds of the controller override those of the data subject."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 18, point 1d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 18 (Right to restriction of processing), point 1d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_18>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_18> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_18/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where processing has been restricted under paragraph 1, such personal data shall, with the exception of storage, only be processed with the data subject's consent or for the establishment, exercise or defence of legal claims or for the protection of the rights of another natural or legal person or for reasons of important public interest of the Union or of a Member State."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 18, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 18 (Right to restriction of processing), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_18>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_18> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_18/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "A data subject who has obtained restriction of processing pursuant to paragraph 1 shall be informed by the controller before the restriction of processing is lifted."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 18, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 18 (Right to restriction of processing), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_18>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_18> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_19/Point_text_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The controller shall communicate any rectification or erasure of personal data or restriction of processing carried out in accordance with Article 16, Article 17(1) and Article 18 to each recipient to whom the personal data have been disclosed, unless this proves impossible or involves disproportionate effort. The controller shall inform the data subject about those recipients if the data subject requests it."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 19, point text_1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 19 (Notification obligation regarding rectification or erasure of personal data or restriction of processing), point text_1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_19>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_19> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_20/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The data subject shall have the right to receive the personal data concerning him or her, which he or she has provided to a controller, in a structured, commonly used and machine-readable format and have the right to transmit those data to another controller without hindrance from the controller to which the personal data have been provided, where:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 20, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 20 (Right to data portability), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_20>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_20> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_20/Point_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the processing is based on consent pursuant to point (a) of Article 6(1) or point (a) of Article 9(2) or on a contract pursuant to point (b) of Article 6(1); and"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 20, point 1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 20 (Right to data portability), point 1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_20>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_20> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_20/Point_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the processing is carried out by automated means."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 20, point 1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 20 (Right to data portability), point 1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_20>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_20> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_20/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "In exercising his or her right to data portability pursuant to paragraph 1, the data subject shall have the right to have the personal data transmitted directly from one controller to another, where technically feasible."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 20, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 20 (Right to data portability), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_20>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_20> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_20/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The exercise of the right referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article shall be without prejudice to Article 17. That right shall not apply to processing necessary for the performance of a task carried out in the public interest or in the exercise of official authority vested in the controller."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 20, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 20 (Right to data portability), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_20>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_20> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_20/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The right referred to in paragraph 1 shall not adversely affect the rights and freedoms of others."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 20, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 20 (Right to data portability), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_20>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_20> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_21/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The data subject shall have the right to object, on grounds relating to his or her particular situation, at any time to processing of personal data concerning him or her which is based on point (e) or (f) of Article 6(1), including profiling based on those provisions. The controller shall no longer process the personal data unless the controller demonstrates compelling legitimate grounds for the processing which override the interests, rights and freedoms of the data subject or for the establishment, exercise or defence of legal claims."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 21, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 21 (Right to object), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_21>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_21> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_21/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where personal data are processed for direct marketing purposes, the data subject shall have the right to object at any time to processing of personal data concerning him or her for such marketing, which includes profiling to the extent that it is related to such direct marketing."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 21, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 21 (Right to object), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_21>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_21> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_21/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where the data subject objects to processing for direct marketing purposes, the personal data shall no longer be processed for such purposes."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 21, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 21 (Right to object), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_21>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_21> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_21/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "At the latest at the time of the first communication with the data subject, the right referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2 shall be explicitly brought to the attention of the data subject and shall be presented clearly and separately from any other information."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 21, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 21 (Right to object), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_21>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_21> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_21/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "In the context of the use of information society services, and notwithstanding Directive 2002/58/EC, the data subject may exercise his or her right to object by automated means using technical specifications."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 21, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 21 (Right to object), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_21>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_21> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_21/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where personal data are processed for scientific or historical research purposes or statistical purposes pursuant to Article 89(1), the data subject, on grounds relating to his or her particular situation, shall have the right to object to processing of personal data concerning him or her, unless the processing is necessary for the performance of a task carried out for reasons of public interest."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 21, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 21 (Right to object), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_21>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_21> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_22/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The data subject shall have the right not to be subject to a decision based solely on automated processing, including profiling, which produces legal effects concerning him or her or similarly significantly affects him or her."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 22, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 22 (Automated individual decision-making, including profiling), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_22>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_22> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_22/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Paragraph 1 shall not apply if the decision:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 22, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 22 (Automated individual decision-making, including profiling), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_22>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_22> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_22/Point_2a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "is necessary for entering into, or performance of, a contract between the data subject and a data controller;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 22, point 2a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 22 (Automated individual decision-making, including profiling), point 2a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_22>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_22> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_22/Point_2b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "is authorised by Union or Member State law to which the controller is subject and which also lays down suitable measures to safeguard the data subject's rights and freedoms and legitimate interests; or"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 22, point 2b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 22 (Automated individual decision-making, including profiling), point 2b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_22>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_22> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_22/Point_2c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "is based on the data subject's explicit consent."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 22, point 2c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 22 (Automated individual decision-making, including profiling), point 2c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_22>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_22> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_22/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "In the cases referred to in points (a) and (c) of paragraph 2, the data controller shall implement suitable measures to safeguard the data subject's rights and freedoms and legitimate interests, at least the right to obtain human intervention on the part of the controller, to express his or her point of view and to contest the decision."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 22, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 22 (Automated individual decision-making, including profiling), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_22>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_22> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_22/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Decisions referred to in paragraph 2 shall not be based on special categories of personal data referred to in Article 9(1), unless point (a) or (g) of Article 9(2) applies and suitable measures to safeguard the data subject's rights and freedoms and legitimate interests are in place."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 22, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 22 (Automated individual decision-making, including profiling), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_22>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_22> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Union or Member State law to which the data controller or processor is subject may restrict by way of a legislative measure the scope of the obligations and rights provided for in Articles 12 to 22 and Article 34, as well as Article 5 in so far as its provisions correspond to the rights and obligations provided for in Articles 12 to 22, when such a restriction respects the essence of the fundamental rights and freedoms and is a necessary and proportionate measure in a democratic society to safeguard:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 23, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 23 (Restrictions), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_23> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23/Point_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "national security;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 23, point 1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 23 (Restrictions), point 1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_23> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23/Point_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "defence;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 23, point 1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 23 (Restrictions), point 1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_23> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23/Point_1c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "public security;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 23, point 1c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 23 (Restrictions), point 1c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_23> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23/Point_1d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the prevention, investigation, detection or prosecution of criminal offences or the execution of criminal penalties, including the safeguarding against and the prevention of threats to public security;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 23, point 1d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 23 (Restrictions), point 1d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_23> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23/Point_1e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "other important objectives of general public interest of the Union or of a Member State, in particular an important economic or financial interest of the Union or of a Member State, including monetary, budgetary and taxation a matters, public health and social security;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 23, point 1e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 23 (Restrictions), point 1e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_23> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23/Point_1f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the protection of judicial independence and judicial proceedings;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 23, point 1f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 23 (Restrictions), point 1f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_23> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23/Point_1g>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the prevention, investigation, detection and prosecution of breaches of ethics for regulated professions;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 23, point 1g"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 23 (Restrictions), point 1g"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_23> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23/Point_1h>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "a monitoring, inspection or regulatory function connected, even occasionally, to the exercise of official authority in the cases referred to in points (a) to (e) and (g);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 23, point 1h"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 23 (Restrictions), point 1h"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_23> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23/Point_1i>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the protection of the data subject or the rights and freedoms of others;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 23, point 1i"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 23 (Restrictions), point 1i"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_23> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23/Point_1j>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the enforcement of civil law claims."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 23, point 1j"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 23 (Restrictions), point 1j"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_23> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "In particular, any legislative measure referred to in paragraph 1 shall contain specific provisions at least, where relevant, as to:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 23, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 23 (Restrictions), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_23> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23/Point_2a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the purposes of the processing or categories of processing;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 23, point 2a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 23 (Restrictions), point 2a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_23> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23/Point_2b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the categories of personal data;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 23, point 2b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 23 (Restrictions), point 2b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_23> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23/Point_2c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the scope of the restrictions introduced;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 23, point 2c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 23 (Restrictions), point 2c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_23> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23/Point_2d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the safeguards to prevent abuse or unlawful access or transfer;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 23, point 2d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 23 (Restrictions), point 2d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_23> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23/Point_2e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the specification of the controller or categories of controllers;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 23, point 2e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 23 (Restrictions), point 2e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_23> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23/Point_2f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the storage periods and the applicable safeguards taking into account the nature, scope and purposes of the processing or categories of processing;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 23, point 2f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 23 (Restrictions), point 2f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_23> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23/Point_2g>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the risks to the rights and freedoms of data subjects; and"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 23, point 2g"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 23 (Restrictions), point 2g"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_23> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23/Point_2h>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the right of data subjects to be informed about the restriction, unless that may be prejudicial to the purpose of the restriction."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter III, article 23, point 2h"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter III (Rights of the data subject), article 23 (Restrictions), point 2h"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_III/Article_23>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iii_article_23> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_24/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Taking into account the nature, scope, context and purposes of processing as well as the risks of varying likelihood and severity for the rights and freedoms of natural persons, the controller shall implement appropriate technical and organisational measures to ensure and to be able to demonstrate that processing is performed in accordance with this Regulation. Those measures shall be reviewed and updated where necessary."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 24, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 24 (Responsibility of the controller), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_24>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_24> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_24/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where proportionate in relation to processing activities, the measures referred to in paragraph 1 shall include the implementation of appropriate data protection policies by the controller."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 24, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 24 (Responsibility of the controller), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_24>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_24> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_24/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Adherence to approved codes of conduct as referred to in Article 40 or approved certification mechanisms as referred to in Article 42 may be used as an element by which to demonstrate compliance with the obligations of the controller."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 24, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 24 (Responsibility of the controller), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_24>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_24> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_25/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Taking into account the state of the art, the cost of implementation and the nature, scope, context and purposes of processing as well as the risks of varying likelihood and severity for rights and freedoms of natural persons posed by the processing, the controller shall, both at the time of the determination of the means for processing and at the time of the processing itself, implement appropriate technical and organisational measures, such as pseudonymisation, which are designed to implement data-protection principles, such as data minimisation, in an effective manner and to integrate the necessary safeguards into the processing in order to meet the requirements of this Regulation and protect the rights of data subjects."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 25, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 25 (Data protection by design and by default), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_25>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_25> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_25/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The controller shall implement appropriate technical and organisational measures for ensuring that, by default, only personal data which are necessary for each specific purpose of the processing are processed. That obligation applies to the amount of personal data collected, the extent of their processing, the period of their storage and their accessibility. In particular, such measures shall ensure that by default personal data are not made accessible without the individual's intervention to an indefinite number of natural persons."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 25, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 25 (Data protection by design and by default), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_25>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_25> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_25/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "An approved certification mechanism pursuant to Article 42 may be used as an element to demonstrate compliance with the requirements set out in paragraphs 1 and 2 of this Article."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 25, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 25 (Data protection by design and by default), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_25>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_25> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_26/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where two or more controllers jointly determine the purposes and means of processing, they shall be joint controllers. They shall in a transparent manner determine their respective responsibilities for compliance with the obligations under this Regulation, in particular as regards the exercising of the rights of the data subject and their respective duties to provide the information referred to in Articles 13 and 14, by means of an arrangement between them unless, and in so far as, the respective responsibilities of the controllers are determined by Union or Member State law to which the controllers are subject. The arrangement may designate a contact point for data subjects."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 26, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 26 (Joint controllers), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_26>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_26> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_26/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The arrangement referred to in paragraph 1 shall duly reflect the respective roles and relationships of the joint controllers vis-à-vis the data subjects. The essence of the arrangement shall be made available to the data subject."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 26, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 26 (Joint controllers), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_26>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_26> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_26/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Irrespective of the terms of the arrangement referred to in paragraph 1, the data subject may exercise his or her rights under this Regulation in respect of and against each of the controllers."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 26, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 26 (Joint controllers), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_26>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_26> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_27/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where Article 3(2) applies, the controller or the processor shall designate in writing a representative in the Union."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 27, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 27 (Representatives of controllers or processors not established in the Union), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_27>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_27> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_27/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The obligation laid down in paragraph 1 of this Article shall not apply to:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 27, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 27 (Representatives of controllers or processors not established in the Union), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_27>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_27> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_27/Point_2a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "processing which is occasional, does not include, on a large scale, processing of special categories of data as referred to in Article 9(1) or processing of personal data relating to criminal convictions and offences referred to in Article 10, and is unlikely to result in a risk to the rights and freedoms of natural persons, taking into account the nature, context, scope and purposes of the processing; or"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 27, point 2a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 27 (Representatives of controllers or processors not established in the Union), point 2a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_27>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_27> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_27/Point_2b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "a public authority or body."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 27, point 2b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 27 (Representatives of controllers or processors not established in the Union), point 2b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_27>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_27> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_27/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The representative shall be established in one of the Member States where the data subjects, whose personal data are processed in relation to the offering of goods or services to them, or whose behaviour is monitored, are."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 27, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 27 (Representatives of controllers or processors not established in the Union), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_27>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_27> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_27/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The representative shall be mandated by the controller or processor to be addressed in addition to or instead of the controller or the processor by, in particular, supervisory authorities and data subjects, on all issues related to processing, for the purposes of ensuring compliance with this Regulation."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 27, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 27 (Representatives of controllers or processors not established in the Union), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_27>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_27> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_27/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The designation of a representative by the controller or processor shall be without prejudice to legal actions which could be initiated against the controller or the processor themselves."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 27, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 27 (Representatives of controllers or processors not established in the Union), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_27>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_27> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where processing is to be carried out on behalf of a controller, the controller shall use only processors providing sufficient guarantees to implement appropriate technical and organisational measures in such a manner that processing will meet the requirements of this Regulation and ensure the protection of the rights of the data subject."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 28, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 28 (Processor), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_28> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The processor shall not engage another processor without prior specific or general written authorisation of the controller. In the case of general written authorisation, the processor shall inform the controller of any intended changes concerning the addition or replacement of other processors, thereby giving the controller the opportunity to object to such changes."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 28, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 28 (Processor), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_28> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Processing by a processor shall be governed by a contract or other legal act under Union or Member State law, that is binding on the processor with regard to the controller and that sets out the subject-matter and duration of the processing, the nature and purpose of the processing, the type of personal data and categories of data subjects and the obligations and rights of the controller. That contract or other legal act shall stipulate, in particular, that the processor:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 28, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 28 (Processor), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_28> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28/Point_3a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "processes the personal data only on documented instructions from the controller, including with regard to transfers of personal data to a third country or an international organisation, unless required to do so by Union or Member State law to which the processor is subject; in such a case, the processor shall inform the controller of that legal requirement before processing, unless that law prohibits such information on important grounds of public interest;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 28, point 3a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 28 (Processor), point 3a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_28> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28/Point_3b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "ensures that persons authorised to process the personal data have committed themselves to confidentiality or are under an appropriate statutory obligation of confidentiality;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 28, point 3b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 28 (Processor), point 3b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_28> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28/Point_3c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "takes all measures required pursuant to Article 32;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 28, point 3c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 28 (Processor), point 3c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_28> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28/Point_3d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "respects the conditions referred to in paragraphs 2 and 4 for engaging another processor;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 28, point 3d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 28 (Processor), point 3d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_28> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28/Point_3e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "taking into account the nature of the processing, assists the controller by appropriate technical and organisational measures, insofar as this is possible, for the fulfilment of the controller's obligation to respond to requests for exercising the data subject's rights laid down in Chapter III;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 28, point 3e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 28 (Processor), point 3e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_28> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28/Point_3f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "assists the controller in ensuring compliance with the obligations pursuant to Articles 32 to 36 taking into account the nature of processing and the information available to the processor;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 28, point 3f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 28 (Processor), point 3f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_28> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28/Point_3g>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "at the choice of the controller, deletes or returns all the personal data to the controller after the end of the provision of services relating to processing, and deletes existing copies unless Union or Member State law requires storage of the personal data;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 28, point 3g"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 28 (Processor), point 3g"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_28> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28/Point_3h>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "makes available to the controller all information necessary to demonstrate compliance with the obligations laid down in this Article and allow for and contribute to audits, including inspections, conducted by the controller or another auditor mandated by the controller."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 28, point 3h"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 28 (Processor), point 3h"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_28> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28/Point_text_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "With regard to point (h) of the first subparagraph, the processor shall immediately inform the controller if, in its opinion, an instruction infringes this Regulation or other Union or Member State data protection provisions."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 28, point text_4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 28 (Processor), point text_4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_28> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where a processor engages another processor for carrying out specific processing activities on behalf of the controller, the same data protection obligations as set out in the contract or other legal act between the controller and the processor as referred to in paragraph 3 shall be imposed on that other processor by way of a contract or other legal act under Union or Member State law, in particular providing sufficient guarantees to implement appropriate technical and organisational measures in such a manner that the processing will meet the requirements of this Regulation. Where that other processor fails to fulfil its data protection obligations, the initial processor shall remain fully liable to the controller for the performance of that other processor's obligations."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 28, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 28 (Processor), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_28> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Adherence of a processor to an approved code of conduct as referred to in Article 40 or an approved certification mechanism as referred to in Article 42 may be used as an element by which to demonstrate sufficient guarantees as referred to in paragraphs 1 and 4 of this Article."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 28, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 28 (Processor), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_28> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Without prejudice to an individual contract between the controller and the processor, the contract or the other legal act referred to in paragraphs 3 and 4 of this Article may be based, in whole or in part, on standard contractual clauses referred to in paragraphs 7 and 8 of this Article, including when they are part of a certification granted to the controller or processor pursuant to Articles 42 and 43."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 28, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 28 (Processor), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_28> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28/Point_7>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Commission may lay down standard contractual clauses for the matters referred to in paragraph 3 and 4 of this Article and in accordance with the examination procedure referred to in Article 93(2)."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 28, point 7"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 28 (Processor), point 7"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_28> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28/Point_8>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "A supervisory authority may adopt standard contractual clauses for the matters referred to in paragraph 3 and 4 of this Article and in accordance with the consistency mechanism referred to in Article 63."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 28, point 8"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 28 (Processor), point 8"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_28> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28/Point_9>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The contract or the other legal act referred to in paragraphs 3 and 4 shall be in writing, including in electronic form."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 28, point 9"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 28 (Processor), point 9"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_28> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28/Point_10>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Without prejudice to Articles 82, 83 and 84, if a processor infringes this Regulation by determining the purposes and means of processing, the processor shall be considered to be a controller in respect of that processing."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 28, point 10"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 28 (Processor), point 10"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_28>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_28> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_29/Point_text_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The processor and any person acting under the authority of the controller or of the processor, who has access to personal data, shall not process those data except on instructions from the controller, unless required to do so by Union or Member State law."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 29, point text_1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 29 (Processing under the authority of the controller or processor), point text_1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_29>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_29> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each controller and, where applicable, the controller's representative, shall maintain a record of processing activities under its responsibility. That record shall contain all of the following information:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 30, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 30 (Records of processing activities), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_30> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30/Point_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the name and contact details of the controller and, where applicable, the joint controller, the controller's representative and the data protection officer;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 30, point 1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 30 (Records of processing activities), point 1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_30> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30/Point_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the purposes of the processing;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 30, point 1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 30 (Records of processing activities), point 1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_30> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30/Point_1c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "a description of the categories of data subjects and of the categories of personal data;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 30, point 1c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 30 (Records of processing activities), point 1c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_30> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30/Point_1d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the categories of recipients to whom the personal data have been or will be disclosed including recipients in third countries or international organisations;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 30, point 1d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 30 (Records of processing activities), point 1d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_30> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30/Point_1e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "where applicable, transfers of personal data to a third country or an international organisation, including the identification of that third country or international organisation and, in the case of transfers referred to in the second subparagraph of Article 49(1), the documentation of suitable safeguards;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 30, point 1e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 30 (Records of processing activities), point 1e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_30> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30/Point_1f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "where possible, the envisaged time limits for erasure of the different categories of data;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 30, point 1f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 30 (Records of processing activities), point 1f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_30> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30/Point_1g>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "where possible, a general description of the technical and organisational security measures referred to in Article 32(1)."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 30, point 1g"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 30 (Records of processing activities), point 1g"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_30> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each processor and, where applicable, the processor's representative shall maintain a record of all categories of processing activities carried out on behalf of a controller, containing:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 30, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 30 (Records of processing activities), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_30> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30/Point_2a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the name and contact details of the processor or processors and of each controller on behalf of which the processor is acting, and, where applicable, of the controller's or the processor's representative, and the data protection officer;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 30, point 2a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 30 (Records of processing activities), point 2a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_30> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30/Point_2b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the categories of processing carried out on behalf of each controller;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 30, point 2b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 30 (Records of processing activities), point 2b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_30> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30/Point_2c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "where applicable, transfers of personal data to a third country or an international organisation, including the identification of that third country or international organisation and, in the case of transfers referred to in the second subparagraph of Article 49(1), the documentation of suitable safeguards;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 30, point 2c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 30 (Records of processing activities), point 2c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_30> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30/Point_2d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "where possible, a general description of the technical and organisational security measures referred to in Article 32(1)."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 30, point 2d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 30 (Records of processing activities), point 2d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_30> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The records referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2 shall be in writing, including in electronic form."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 30, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 30 (Records of processing activities), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_30> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The controller or the processor and, where applicable, the controller's or the processor's representative, shall make the record available to the supervisory authority on request."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 30, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 30 (Records of processing activities), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_30> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The obligations referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2 shall not apply to an enterprise or an organisation employing fewer than 250 persons unless the processing it carries out is likely to result in a risk to the rights and freedoms of data subjects, the processing is not occasional, or the processing includes special categories of data as referred to in Article 9(1) or personal data relating to criminal convictions and offences referred to in Article 10."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 30, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 30 (Records of processing activities), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_30>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_30> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_31/Point_text_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The controller and the processor and, where applicable, their representatives, shall cooperate, on request, with the supervisory authority in the performance of its tasks."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 31, point text_1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 31 (Cooperation with the supervisory authority), point text_1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_31>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_31> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_32/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Taking into account the state of the art, the costs of implementation and the nature, scope, context and purposes of processing as well as the risk of varying likelihood and severity for the rights and freedoms of natural persons, the controller and the processor shall implement appropriate technical and organisational measures to ensure a level of security appropriate to the risk, including inter alia as appropriate:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 32, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 32 (Security of processing), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_32>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_32> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_32/Point_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the pseudonymisation and encryption of personal data;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 32, point 1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 32 (Security of processing), point 1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_32>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_32> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_32/Point_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the ability to ensure the ongoing confidentiality, integrity, availability and resilience of processing systems and services;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 32, point 1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 32 (Security of processing), point 1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_32>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_32> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_32/Point_1c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the ability to restore the availability and access to personal data in a timely manner in the event of a physical or technical incident;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 32, point 1c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 32 (Security of processing), point 1c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_32>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_32> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_32/Point_1d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "a process for regularly testing, assessing and evaluating the effectiveness of technical and organisational measures for ensuring the security of the processing."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 32, point 1d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 32 (Security of processing), point 1d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_32>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_32> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_32/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "In assessing the appropriate level of security account shall be taken in particular of the risks that are presented by processing, in particular from accidental or unlawful destruction, loss, alteration, unauthorised disclosure of, or access to personal data transmitted, stored or otherwise processed."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 32, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 32 (Security of processing), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_32>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_32> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_32/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Adherence to an approved code of conduct as referred to in Article 40 or an approved certification mechanism as referred to in Article 42 may be used as an element by which to demonstrate compliance with the requirements set out in paragraph 1 of this Article."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 32, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 32 (Security of processing), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_32>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_32> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_32/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The controller and processor shall take steps to ensure that any natural person acting under the authority of the controller or the processor who has access to personal data does not process them except on instructions from the controller, unless he or she is required to do so by Union or Member State law."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 32, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 32 (Security of processing), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_32>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_32> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_33/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "In the case of a personal data breach, the controller shall without undue delay and, where feasible, not later than 72 hours after having become aware of it, notify the personal data breach to the supervisory authority competent in accordance with Article 55, unless the personal data breach is unlikely to result in a risk to the rights and freedoms of natural persons. Where the notification to the supervisory authority is not made within 72 hours, it shall be accompanied by reasons for the delay."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 33, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 33 (Notification of a personal data breach to the supervisory authority), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_33>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_33> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_33/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The processor shall notify the controller without undue delay after becoming aware of a personal data breach."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 33, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 33 (Notification of a personal data breach to the supervisory authority), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_33>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_33> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_33/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The notification referred to in paragraph 1 shall at least:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 33, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 33 (Notification of a personal data breach to the supervisory authority), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_33>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_33> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_33/Point_3a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "describe the nature of the personal data breach including where possible, the categories and approximate number of data subjects concerned and the categories and approximate number of personal data records concerned;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 33, point 3a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 33 (Notification of a personal data breach to the supervisory authority), point 3a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_33>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_33> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_33/Point_3b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "communicate the name and contact details of the data protection officer or other contact point where more information can be obtained;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 33, point 3b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 33 (Notification of a personal data breach to the supervisory authority), point 3b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_33>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_33> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_33/Point_3c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "describe the likely consequences of the personal data breach;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 33, point 3c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 33 (Notification of a personal data breach to the supervisory authority), point 3c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_33>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_33> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_33/Point_3d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "describe the measures taken or proposed to be taken by the controller to address the personal data breach, including, where appropriate, measures to mitigate its possible adverse effects."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 33, point 3d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 33 (Notification of a personal data breach to the supervisory authority), point 3d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_33>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_33> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_33/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where, and in so far as, it is not possible to provide the information at the same time, the information may be provided in phases without undue further delay."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 33, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 33 (Notification of a personal data breach to the supervisory authority), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_33>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_33> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_33/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The controller shall document any personal data breaches, comprising the facts relating to the personal data breach, its effects and the remedial action taken. That documentation shall enable the supervisory authority to verify compliance with this Article."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 33, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 33 (Notification of a personal data breach to the supervisory authority), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_33>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_33> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_34/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "When the personal data breach is likely to result in a high risk to the rights and freedoms of natural persons, the controller shall communicate the personal data breach to the data subject without undue delay."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 34, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 34 (Communication of a personal data breach to the data subject), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_34>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_34> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_34/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The communication to the data subject referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article shall describe in clear and plain language the nature of the personal data breach and contain at least the information and measures referred to in points (b), (c) and (d) of Article 33(3)."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 34, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 34 (Communication of a personal data breach to the data subject), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_34>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_34> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_34/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The communication to the data subject referred to in paragraph 1 shall not be required if any of the following conditions are met:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 34, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 34 (Communication of a personal data breach to the data subject), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_34>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_34> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_34/Point_3a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the controller has implemented appropriate technical and organisational protection measures, and those measures were applied to the personal data affected by the personal data breach, in particular those that render the personal data unintelligible to any person who is not authorised to access it, such as encryption;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 34, point 3a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 34 (Communication of a personal data breach to the data subject), point 3a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_34>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_34> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_34/Point_3b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the controller has taken subsequent measures which ensure that the high risk to the rights and freedoms of data subjects referred to in paragraph 1 is no longer likely to materialise;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 34, point 3b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 34 (Communication of a personal data breach to the data subject), point 3b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_34>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_34> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_34/Point_3c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "it would involve disproportionate effort. In such a case, there shall instead be a public communication or similar measure whereby the data subjects are informed in an equally effective manner."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 34, point 3c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 34 (Communication of a personal data breach to the data subject), point 3c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_34>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_34> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_34/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "If the controller has not already communicated the personal data breach to the data subject, the supervisory authority, having considered the likelihood of the personal data breach resulting in a high risk, may require it to do so or may decide that any of the conditions referred to in paragraph 3 are met."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 34, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 34 (Communication of a personal data breach to the data subject), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_34>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_34> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where a type of processing in particular using new technologies, and taking into account the nature, scope, context and purposes of the processing, is likely to result in a high risk to the rights and freedoms of natural persons, the controller shall, prior to the processing, carry out an assessment of the impact of the envisaged processing operations on the protection of personal data. A single assessment may address a set of similar processing operations that present similar high risks."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 35, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 35 (Data protection impact assessment), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_35> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The controller shall seek the advice of the data protection officer, where designated, when carrying out a data protection impact assessment."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 35, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 35 (Data protection impact assessment), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_35> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "A data protection impact assessment referred to in paragraph 1 shall in particular be required in the case of:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 35, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 35 (Data protection impact assessment), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_35> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35/Point_3a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "a systematic and extensive evaluation of personal aspects relating to natural persons which is based on automated processing, including profiling, and on which decisions are based that produce legal effects concerning the natural person or similarly significantly affect the natural person;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 35, point 3a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 35 (Data protection impact assessment), point 3a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_35> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35/Point_3b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "processing on a large scale of special categories of data referred to in Article 9(1), or of personal data relating to criminal convictions and offences referred to in Article 10; or"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 35, point 3b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 35 (Data protection impact assessment), point 3b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_35> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35/Point_3c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "a systematic monitoring of a publicly accessible area on a large scale."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 35, point 3c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 35 (Data protection impact assessment), point 3c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_35> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The supervisory authority shall establish and make public a list of the kind of processing operations which are subject to the requirement for a data protection impact assessment pursuant to paragraph 1. The supervisory authority shall communicate those lists to the Board referred to in Article 68."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 35, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 35 (Data protection impact assessment), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_35> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The supervisory authority may also establish and make public a list of the kind of processing operations for which no data protection impact assessment is required. The supervisory authority shall communicate those lists to the Board."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 35, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 35 (Data protection impact assessment), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_35> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Prior to the adoption of the lists referred to in paragraphs 4 and 5, the competent supervisory authority shall apply the consistency mechanism referred to in Article 63 where such lists involve processing activities which are related to the offering of goods or services to data subjects or to the monitoring of their behaviour in several Member States, or may substantially affect the free movement of personal data within the Union."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 35, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 35 (Data protection impact assessment), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_35> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35/Point_7>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The assessment shall contain at least:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 35, point 7"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 35 (Data protection impact assessment), point 7"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_35> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35/Point_7a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "a systematic description of the envisaged processing operations and the purposes of the processing, including, where applicable, the legitimate interest pursued by the controller;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 35, point 7a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 35 (Data protection impact assessment), point 7a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_35> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35/Point_7b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "an assessment of the necessity and proportionality of the processing operations in relation to the purposes;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 35, point 7b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 35 (Data protection impact assessment), point 7b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_35> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35/Point_7c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "an assessment of the risks to the rights and freedoms of data subjects referred to in paragraph 1; and"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 35, point 7c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 35 (Data protection impact assessment), point 7c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_35> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35/Point_7d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the measures envisaged to address the risks, including safeguards, security measures and mechanisms to ensure the protection of personal data and to demonstrate compliance with this Regulation taking into account the rights and legitimate interests of data subjects and other persons concerned."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 35, point 7d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 35 (Data protection impact assessment), point 7d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_35> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35/Point_8>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Compliance with approved codes of conduct referred to in Article 40 by the relevant controllers or processors shall be taken into due account in assessing the impact of the processing operations performed by such controllers or processors, in particular for the purposes of a data protection impact assessment."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 35, point 8"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 35 (Data protection impact assessment), point 8"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_35> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35/Point_9>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where appropriate, the controller shall seek the views of data subjects or their representatives on the intended processing, without prejudice to the protection of commercial or public interests or the security of processing operations."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 35, point 9"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 35 (Data protection impact assessment), point 9"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_35> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35/Point_10>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where processing pursuant to point (c) or (e) of Article 6(1) has a legal basis in Union law or in the law of the Member State to which the controller is subject, that law regulates the specific processing operation or set of operations in question, and a data protection impact assessment has already been carried out as part of a general impact assessment in the context of the adoption of that legal basis, paragraphs 1 to 7 shall not apply unless Member States deem it to be necessary to carry out such an assessment prior to processing activities."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 35, point 10"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 35 (Data protection impact assessment), point 10"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_35> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35/Point_11>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where necessary, the controller shall carry out a review to assess if processing is performed in accordance with the data protection impact assessment at least when there is a change of the risk represented by processing operations."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 35, point 11"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 35 (Data protection impact assessment), point 11"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_35>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_35> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_36/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The controller shall consult the supervisory authority prior to processing where a data protection impact assessment under Article 35 indicates that the processing would result in a high risk in the absence of measures taken by the controller to mitigate the risk."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 36, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 36 (Prior consultation), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_36>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_36> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_36/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where the supervisory authority is of the opinion that the intended processing referred to in paragraph 1 would infringe this Regulation, in particular where the controller has insufficiently identified or mitigated the risk, the supervisory authority shall, within period of up to eight weeks of receipt of the request for consultation, provide written advice to the controller and, where applicable to the processor, and may use any of its powers referred to in Article 58. That period may be extended by six weeks, taking into account the complexity of the intended processing. The supervisory authority shall inform the controller and, where applicable, the processor, of any such extension within one month of receipt of the request for consultation together with the reasons for the delay. Those periods may be suspended until the supervisory authority has obtained information it has requested for the purposes of the consultation."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 36, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 36 (Prior consultation), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_36>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_36> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_36/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "When consulting the supervisory authority pursuant to paragraph 1, the controller shall provide the supervisory authority with:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 36, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 36 (Prior consultation), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_36>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_36> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_36/Point_3a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "where applicable, the respective responsibilities of the controller, joint controllers and processors involved in the processing, in particular for processing within a group of undertakings;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 36, point 3a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 36 (Prior consultation), point 3a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_36>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_36> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_36/Point_3b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the purposes and means of the intended processing;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 36, point 3b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 36 (Prior consultation), point 3b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_36>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_36> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_36/Point_3c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the measures and safeguards provided to protect the rights and freedoms of data subjects pursuant to this Regulation;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 36, point 3c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 36 (Prior consultation), point 3c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_36>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_36> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_36/Point_3d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "where applicable, the contact details of the data protection officer;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 36, point 3d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 36 (Prior consultation), point 3d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_36>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_36> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_36/Point_3e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the data protection impact assessment provided for in Article 35; and"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 36, point 3e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 36 (Prior consultation), point 3e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_36>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_36> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_36/Point_3f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "any other information requested by the supervisory authority."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 36, point 3f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 36 (Prior consultation), point 3f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_36>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_36> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_36/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Member States shall consult the supervisory authority during the preparation of a proposal for a legislative measure to be adopted by a national parliament, or of a regulatory measure based on such a legislative measure, which relates to processing."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 36, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 36 (Prior consultation), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_36>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_36> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_36/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Notwithstanding paragraph 1, Member State law may require controllers to consult with, and obtain prior authorisation from, the supervisory authority in relation to processing by a controller for the performance of a task carried out by the controller in the public interest, including processing in relation to social protection and public health."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 36, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 36 (Prior consultation), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_36>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_36> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_37/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The controller and the processor shall designate a data protection officer in any case where:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 37, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 37 (Designation of the data protection officer), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_37>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_37> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_37/Point_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the processing is carried out by a public authority or body, except for courts acting in their judicial capacity;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 37, point 1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 37 (Designation of the data protection officer), point 1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_37>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_37> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_37/Point_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the core activities of the controller or the processor consist of processing operations which, by virtue of their nature, their scope and/or their purposes, require regular and systematic monitoring of data subjects on a large scale; or"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 37, point 1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 37 (Designation of the data protection officer), point 1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_37>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_37> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_37/Point_1c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the core activities of the controller or the processor consist of processing on a large scale of special categories of data pursuant to Article 9 and personal data relating to criminal convictions and offences referred to in Article 10."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 37, point 1c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 37 (Designation of the data protection officer), point 1c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_37>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_37> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_37/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "A group of undertakings may appoint a single data protection officer provided that a data protection officer is easily accessible from each establishment."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 37, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 37 (Designation of the data protection officer), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_37>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_37> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_37/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where the controller or the processor is a public authority or body, a single data protection officer may be designated for several such authorities or bodies, taking account of their organisational structure and size."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 37, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 37 (Designation of the data protection officer), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_37>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_37> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_37/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "In cases other than those referred to in paragraph 1, the controller or processor or associations and other bodies representing categories of controllers or processors may or, where required by Union or Member State law shall, designate a data protection officer. The data protection officer may act for such associations and other bodies representing controllers or processors."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 37, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 37 (Designation of the data protection officer), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_37>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_37> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_37/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The data protection officer shall be designated on the basis of professional qualities and, in particular, expert knowledge of data protection law and practices and the ability to fulfil the tasks referred to in Article 39."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 37, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 37 (Designation of the data protection officer), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_37>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_37> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_37/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The data protection officer may be a staff member of the controller or processor, or fulfil the tasks on the basis of a service contract."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 37, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 37 (Designation of the data protection officer), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_37>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_37> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_37/Point_7>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The controller or the processor shall publish the contact details of the data protection officer and communicate them to the supervisory authority."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 37, point 7"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 37 (Designation of the data protection officer), point 7"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_37>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_37> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_38/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The controller and the processor shall ensure that the data protection officer is involved, properly and in a timely manner, in all issues which relate to the protection of personal data."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 38, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 38 (Position of the data protection officer), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_38>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_38> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_38/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The controller and processor shall support the data protection officer in performing the tasks referred to in Article 39 by providing resources necessary to carry out those tasks and access to personal data and processing operations, and to maintain his or her expert knowledge."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 38, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 38 (Position of the data protection officer), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_38>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_38> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_38/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The controller and processor shall ensure that the data protection officer does not receive any instructions regarding the exercise of those tasks. He or she shall not be dismissed or penalised by the controller or the processor for performing his tasks. The data protection officer shall directly report to the highest management level of the controller or the processor."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 38, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 38 (Position of the data protection officer), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_38>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_38> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_38/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Data subjects may contact the data protection officer with regard to all issues related to processing of their personal data and to the exercise of their rights under this Regulation."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 38, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 38 (Position of the data protection officer), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_38>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_38> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_38/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The data protection officer shall be bound by secrecy or confidentiality concerning the performance of his or her tasks, in accordance with Union or Member State law."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 38, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 38 (Position of the data protection officer), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_38>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_38> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_38/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The data protection officer may fulfil other tasks and duties. The controller or processor shall ensure that any such tasks and duties do not result in a conflict of interests."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 38, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 38 (Position of the data protection officer), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_38>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_38> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_39/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The data protection officer shall have at least the following tasks:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 39, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 39 (Tasks of the data protection officer), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_39>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_39> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_39/Point_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to inform and advise the controller or the processor and the employees who carry out processing of their obligations pursuant to this Regulation and to other Union or Member State data protection provisions;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 39, point 1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 39 (Tasks of the data protection officer), point 1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_39>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_39> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_39/Point_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to monitor compliance with this Regulation, with other Union or Member State data protection provisions and with the policies of the controller or processor in relation to the protection of personal data, including the assignment of responsibilities, awareness-raising and training of staff involved in processing operations, and the related audits;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 39, point 1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 39 (Tasks of the data protection officer), point 1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_39>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_39> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_39/Point_1c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to provide advice where requested as regards the data protection impact assessment and monitor its performance pursuant to Article 35;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 39, point 1c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 39 (Tasks of the data protection officer), point 1c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_39>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_39> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_39/Point_1d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to cooperate with the supervisory authority;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 39, point 1d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 39 (Tasks of the data protection officer), point 1d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_39>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_39> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_39/Point_1e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to act as the contact point for the supervisory authority on issues relating to processing, including the prior consultation referred to in Article 36, and to consult, where appropriate, with regard to any other matter."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 39, point 1e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 39 (Tasks of the data protection officer), point 1e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_39>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_39> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_39/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The data protection officer shall in the performance of his or her tasks have due regard to the risk associated with processing operations, taking into account the nature, scope, context and purposes of processing."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 39, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 39 (Tasks of the data protection officer), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_39>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_39> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Member States, the supervisory authorities, the Board and the Commission shall encourage the drawing up of codes of conduct intended to contribute to the proper application of this Regulation, taking account of the specific features of the various processing sectors and the specific needs of micro, small and medium-sized enterprises."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 40, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 40 (Codes of conduct), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_40> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Associations and other bodies representing categories of controllers or processors may prepare codes of conduct, or amend or extend such codes, for the purpose of specifying the application of this Regulation, such as with regard to:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 40, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 40 (Codes of conduct), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_40> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40/Point_2a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "fair and transparent processing;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 40, point 2a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 40 (Codes of conduct), point 2a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_40> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40/Point_2b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the legitimate interests pursued by controllers in specific contexts;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 40, point 2b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 40 (Codes of conduct), point 2b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_40> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40/Point_2c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the collection of personal data;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 40, point 2c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 40 (Codes of conduct), point 2c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_40> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40/Point_2d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the pseudonymisation of personal data;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 40, point 2d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 40 (Codes of conduct), point 2d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_40> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40/Point_2e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the information provided to the public and to data subjects;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 40, point 2e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 40 (Codes of conduct), point 2e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_40> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40/Point_2f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the exercise of the rights of data subjects;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 40, point 2f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 40 (Codes of conduct), point 2f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_40> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40/Point_2g>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the information provided to, and the protection of, children, and the manner in which the consent of the holders of parental responsibility over children is to be obtained;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 40, point 2g"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 40 (Codes of conduct), point 2g"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_40> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40/Point_2h>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the measures and procedures referred to in Articles 24 and 25 and the measures to ensure security of processing referred to in Article 32;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 40, point 2h"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 40 (Codes of conduct), point 2h"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_40> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40/Point_2i>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the notification of personal data breaches to supervisory authorities and the communication of such personal data breaches to data subjects;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 40, point 2i"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 40 (Codes of conduct), point 2i"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_40> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40/Point_2j>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the transfer of personal data to third countries or international organisations; or"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 40, point 2j"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 40 (Codes of conduct), point 2j"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_40> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40/Point_2k>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "out-of-court proceedings and other dispute resolution procedures for resolving disputes between controllers and data subjects with regard to processing, without prejudice to the rights of data subjects pursuant to Articles 77 and 79."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 40, point 2k"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 40 (Codes of conduct), point 2k"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_40> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "In addition to adherence by controllers or processors subject to this Regulation, codes of conduct approved pursuant to paragraph 5 of this Article and having general validity pursuant to paragraph 9 of this Article may also be adhered to by controllers or processors that are not subject to this Regulation pursuant to Article 3 in order to provide appropriate safeguards within the framework of personal data transfers to third countries or international organisations under the terms referred to in point (e) of Article 46(2). Such controllers or processors shall make binding and enforceable commitments, via contractual or other legally binding instruments, to apply those appropriate safeguards including with regard to the rights of data subjects."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 40, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 40 (Codes of conduct), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_40> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "A code of conduct referred to in paragraph 2 of this Article shall contain mechanisms which enable the body referred to in Article 41(1) to carry out the mandatory monitoring of compliance with its provisions by the controllers or processors which undertake to apply it, without prejudice to the tasks and powers of supervisory authorities competent pursuant to Article 55 or 56."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 40, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 40 (Codes of conduct), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_40> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Associations and other bodies referred to in paragraph 2 of this Article which intend to prepare a code of conduct or to amend or extend an existing code shall submit the draft code, amendment or extension to the supervisory authority which is competent pursuant to Article 55. The supervisory authority shall provide an opinion on whether the draft code, amendment or extension complies with this Regulation and shall approve that draft code, amendment or extension if it finds that it provides sufficient appropriate safeguards."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 40, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 40 (Codes of conduct), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_40> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where the draft code, or amendment or extension is approved in accordance with paragraph 5, and where the code of conduct concerned does not relate to processing activities in several Member States, the supervisory authority shall register and publish the code."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 40, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 40 (Codes of conduct), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_40> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40/Point_7>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where a draft code of conduct relates to processing activities in several Member States, the supervisory authority which is competent pursuant to Article 55 shall, before approving the draft code, amendment or extension, submit it in the procedure referred to in Article 63 to the Board which shall provide an opinion on whether the draft code, amendment or extension complies with this Regulation or, in the situation referred to in paragraph 3 of this Article, provides appropriate safeguards."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 40, point 7"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 40 (Codes of conduct), point 7"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_40> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40/Point_8>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where the opinion referred to in paragraph 7 confirms that the draft code, amendment or extension complies with this Regulation, or, in the situation referred to in paragraph 3, provides appropriate safeguards, the Board shall submit its opinion to the Commission."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 40, point 8"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 40 (Codes of conduct), point 8"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_40> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40/Point_9>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Commission may, by way of implementing acts, decide that the approved code of conduct, amendment or extension submitted to it pursuant to paragraph 8 of this Article have general validity within the Union. Those implementing acts shall be adopted in accordance with the examination procedure set out in Article 93(2)."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 40, point 9"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 40 (Codes of conduct), point 9"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_40> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40/Point_10>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Commission shall ensure appropriate publicity for the approved codes which have been decided as having general validity in accordance with paragraph 9."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 40, point 10"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 40 (Codes of conduct), point 10"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_40> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40/Point_11>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Board shall collate all approved codes of conduct, amendments and extensions in a register and shall make them publicly available by way of appropriate means."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 40, point 11"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 40 (Codes of conduct), point 11"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_40>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_40> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_41/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Without prejudice to the tasks and powers of the competent supervisory authority under Articles 57 and 58, the monitoring of compliance with a code of conduct pursuant to Article 40 may be carried out by a body which has an appropriate level of expertise in relation to the subject-matter of the code and is accredited for that purpose by the competent supervisory authority."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 41, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 41 (Monitoring of approved codes of conduct), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_41>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_41> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_41/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "A body as referred to in paragraph 1 may be accredited to monitor compliance with a code of conduct where that body has:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 41, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 41 (Monitoring of approved codes of conduct), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_41>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_41> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_41/Point_2a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "demonstrated its independence and expertise in relation to the subject-matter of the code to the satisfaction of the competent supervisory authority;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 41, point 2a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 41 (Monitoring of approved codes of conduct), point 2a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_41>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_41> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_41/Point_2b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "established procedures which allow it to assess the eligibility of controllers and processors concerned to apply the code, to monitor their compliance with its provisions and to periodically review its operation;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 41, point 2b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 41 (Monitoring of approved codes of conduct), point 2b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_41>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_41> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_41/Point_2c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "established procedures and structures to handle complaints about infringements of the code or the manner in which the code has been, or is being, implemented by a controller or processor, and to make those procedures and structures transparent to data subjects and the public; and"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 41, point 2c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 41 (Monitoring of approved codes of conduct), point 2c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_41>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_41> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_41/Point_2d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "demonstrated to the satisfaction of the competent supervisory authority that its tasks and duties do not result in a conflict of interests."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 41, point 2d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 41 (Monitoring of approved codes of conduct), point 2d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_41>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_41> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_41/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The competent supervisory authority shall submit the draft criteria for accreditation of a body as referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article to the Board pursuant to the consistency mechanism referred to in Article 63."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 41, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 41 (Monitoring of approved codes of conduct), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_41>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_41> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_41/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Without prejudice to the tasks and powers of the competent supervisory authority and the provisions of Chapter VIII, a body as referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article shall, subject to appropriate safeguards, take appropriate action in cases of infringement of the code by a controller or processor, including suspension or exclusion of the controller or processor concerned from the code. It shall inform the competent supervisory authority of such actions and the reasons for taking them."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 41, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 41 (Monitoring of approved codes of conduct), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_41>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_41> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_41/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The competent supervisory authority shall revoke the accreditation of a body as referred to in paragraph 1 if the conditions for accreditation are not, or are no longer, met or where actions taken by the body infringe this Regulation."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 41, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 41 (Monitoring of approved codes of conduct), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_41>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_41> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_41/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "This Article shall not apply to processing carried out by public authorities and bodies."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 41, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 41 (Monitoring of approved codes of conduct), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_41>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_41> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_42/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Member States, the supervisory authorities, the Board and the Commission shall encourage, in particular at Union level, the establishment of data protection certification mechanisms and of data protection seals and marks, for the purpose of demonstrating compliance with this Regulation of processing operations by controllers and processors. The specific needs of micro, small and medium-sized enterprises shall be taken into account."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 42, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 42 (Certification), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_42>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_42> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_42/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "In addition to adherence by controllers or processors subject to this Regulation, data protection certification mechanisms, seals or marks approved pursuant to paragraph 5 of this Article may be established for the purpose of demonstrating the existence of appropriate safeguards provided by controllers or processors that are not subject to this Regulation pursuant to Article 3 within the framework of personal data transfers to third countries or international organisations under the terms referred to in point (f) of Article 46(2). Such controllers or processors shall make binding and enforceable commitments, via contractual or other legally binding instruments, to apply those appropriate safeguards, including with regard to the rights of data subjects."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 42, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 42 (Certification), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_42>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_42> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_42/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The certification shall be voluntary and available via a process that is transparent."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 42, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 42 (Certification), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_42>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_42> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_42/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "A certification pursuant to this Article does not reduce the responsibility of the controller or the processor for compliance with this Regulation and is without prejudice to the tasks and powers of the supervisory authorities which are competent pursuant to Article 55 or 56."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 42, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 42 (Certification), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_42>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_42> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_42/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "A certification pursuant to this Article shall be issued by the certification bodies referred to in Article 43 or by the competent supervisory authority, on the basis of criteria approved by that competent supervisory authority pursuant to Article 58(3) or by the Board pursuant to Article 63. Where the criteria are approved by the Board, this may result in a common certification, the European Data Protection Seal."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 42, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 42 (Certification), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_42>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_42> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_42/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The controller or processor which submits its processing to the certification mechanism shall provide the certification body referred to in Article 43, or where applicable, the competent supervisory authority, with all information and access to its processing activities which are necessary to conduct the certification procedure."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 42, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 42 (Certification), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_42>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_42> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_42/Point_7>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Certification shall be issued to a controller or processor for a maximum period of three years and may be renewed, under the same conditions, provided that the relevant requirements continue to be met. Certification shall be withdrawn, as applicable, by the certification bodies referred to in Article 43 or by the competent supervisory authority where the requirements for the certification are not or are no longer met."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 42, point 7"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 42 (Certification), point 7"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_42>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_42> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_42/Point_8>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Board shall collate all certification mechanisms and data protection seals and marks in a register and shall make them publicly available by any appropriate means."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 42, point 8"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 42 (Certification), point 8"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_42>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_42> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Without prejudice to the tasks and powers of the competent supervisory authority under Articles 57 and 58, certification bodies which have an appropriate level of expertise in relation to data protection shall, after informing the supervisory authority in order to allow it to exercise its powers pursuant to point (h) of Article 58(2) where necessary, issue and renew certification. Member States shall ensure that those certification bodies are accredited by one or both of the following:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 43, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 43 (Certification bodies), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_43> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43/Point_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the supervisory authority which is competent pursuant to Article 55 or 56;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 43, point 1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 43 (Certification bodies), point 1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_43> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43/Point_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the national accreditation body named in accordance with Regulation (EC) No 765/2008 of the European Parliament and of the Council (20) in accordance with EN-ISO/IEC 17065/2012 and with the additional requirements established by the supervisory authority which is competent pursuant to Article 55 or 56."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 43, point 1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 43 (Certification bodies), point 1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_43> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Certification bodies referred to in paragraph 1 shall be accredited in accordance with that paragraph only where they have:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 43, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 43 (Certification bodies), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_43> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43/Point_2a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "demonstrated their independence and expertise in relation to the subject-matter of the certification to the satisfaction of the competent supervisory authority;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 43, point 2a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 43 (Certification bodies), point 2a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_43> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43/Point_2b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "undertaken to respect the criteria referred to in Article 42(5) and approved by the supervisory authority which is competent pursuant to Article 55 or 56 or by the Board pursuant to Article 63;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 43, point 2b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 43 (Certification bodies), point 2b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_43> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43/Point_2c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "established procedures for the issuing, periodic review and withdrawal of data protection certification, seals and marks;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 43, point 2c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 43 (Certification bodies), point 2c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_43> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43/Point_2d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "established procedures and structures to handle complaints about infringements of the certification or the manner in which the certification has been, or is being, implemented by the controller or processor, and to make those procedures and structures transparent to data subjects and the public; and"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 43, point 2d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 43 (Certification bodies), point 2d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_43> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43/Point_2e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "demonstrated, to the satisfaction of the competent supervisory authority, that their tasks and duties do not result in a conflict of interests."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 43, point 2e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 43 (Certification bodies), point 2e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_43> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The accreditation of certification bodies as referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2 of this Article shall take place on the basis of criteria approved by the supervisory authority which is competent pursuant to Article 55 or 56 or by the Board pursuant to Article 63. In the case of accreditation pursuant to point (b) of paragraph 1 of this Article, those requirements shall complement those envisaged in Regulation (EC) No 765/2008 and the technical rules that describe the methods and procedures of the certification bodies."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 43, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 43 (Certification bodies), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_43> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The certification bodies referred to in paragraph 1 shall be responsible for the proper assessment leading to the certification or the withdrawal of such certification without prejudice to the responsibility of the controller or processor for compliance with this Regulation. The accreditation shall be issued for a maximum period of five years and may be renewed on the same conditions provided that the certification body meets the requirements set out in this Article."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 43, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 43 (Certification bodies), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_43> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The certification bodies referred to in paragraph 1 shall provide the competent supervisory authorities with the reasons for granting or withdrawing the requested certification."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 43, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 43 (Certification bodies), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_43> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The requirements referred to in paragraph 3 of this Article and the criteria referred to in Article 42(5) shall be made public by the supervisory authority in an easily accessible form. The supervisory authorities shall also transmit those requirements and criteria to the Board. The Board shall collate all certification mechanisms and data protection seals in a register and shall make them publicly available by any appropriate means."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 43, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 43 (Certification bodies), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_43> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43/Point_7>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Without prejudice to Chapter VIII, the competent supervisory authority or the national accreditation body shall revoke an accreditation of a certification body pursuant to paragraph 1 of this Article where the conditions for the accreditation are not, or are no longer, met or where actions taken by a certification body infringe this Regulation."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 43, point 7"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 43 (Certification bodies), point 7"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_43> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43/Point_8>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Commission shall be empowered to adopt delegated acts in accordance with Article 92 for the purpose of specifying the requirements to be taken into account for the data protection certification mechanisms referred to in Article 42(1)."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 43, point 8"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 43 (Certification bodies), point 8"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_43> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43/Point_9>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Commission may adopt implementing acts laying down technical standards for certification mechanisms and data protection seals and marks, and mechanisms to promote and recognise those certification mechanisms, seals and marks. Those implementing acts shall be adopted in accordance with the examination procedure referred to in Article 93(2)."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IV, article 43, point 9"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IV (Controller and processor), article 43 (Certification bodies), point 9"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IV/Article_43>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_iv_article_43> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_44/Point_text_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Any transfer of personal data which are undergoing processing or are intended for processing after transfer to a third country or to an international organisation shall take place only if, subject to the other provisions of this Regulation, the conditions laid down in this Chapter are complied with by the controller and processor, including for onward transfers of personal data from the third country or an international organisation to another third country or to another international organisation. All provisions in this Chapter shall be applied in order to ensure that the level of protection of natural persons guaranteed by this Regulation is not undermined."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 44, point text_1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 44 (General principle for transfers), point text_1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_44>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_44> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "A transfer of personal data to a third country or an international organisation may take place where the Commission has decided that the third country, a territory or one or more specified sectors within that third country, or the international organisation in question ensures an adequate level of protection. Such a transfer shall not require any specific authorisation."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 45, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 45 (Transfers on the basis of an adequacy decision), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_45> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "When assessing the adequacy of the level of protection, the Commission shall, in particular, take account of the following elements:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 45, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 45 (Transfers on the basis of an adequacy decision), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_45> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45/Point_2a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the rule of law, respect for human rights and fundamental freedoms, relevant legislation, both general and sectoral, including concerning public security, defence, national security and criminal law and the access of public authorities to personal data, as well as the implementation of such legislation, data protection rules, professional rules and security measures, including rules for the onward transfer of personal data to another third country or international organisation which are complied with in that country or international organisation, case-law, as well as effective and enforceable data subject rights and effective administrative and judicial redress for the data subjects whose personal data are being transferred;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 45, point 2a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 45 (Transfers on the basis of an adequacy decision), point 2a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_45> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45/Point_2b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the existence and effective functioning of one or more independent supervisory authorities in the third country or to which an international organisation is subject, with responsibility for ensuring and enforcing compliance with the data protection rules, including adequate enforcement powers, for assisting and advising the data subjects in exercising their rights and for cooperation with the supervisory authorities of the Member States; and"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 45, point 2b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 45 (Transfers on the basis of an adequacy decision), point 2b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_45> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45/Point_2c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the international commitments the third country or international organisation concerned has entered into, or other obligations arising from legally binding conventions or instruments as well as from its participation in multilateral or regional systems, in particular in relation to the protection of personal data."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 45, point 2c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 45 (Transfers on the basis of an adequacy decision), point 2c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_45> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Commission, after assessing the adequacy of the level of protection, may decide, by means of implementing act, that a third country, a territory or one or more specified sectors within a third country, or an international organisation ensures an adequate level of protection within the meaning of paragraph 2 of this Article. The implementing act shall provide for a mechanism for a periodic review, at least every four years, which shall take into account all relevant developments in the third country or international organisation. The implementing act shall specify its territorial and sectoral application and, where applicable, identify the supervisory authority or authorities referred to in point (b) of paragraph 2 of this Article. The implementing act shall be adopted in accordance with the examination procedure referred to in Article 93(2)."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 45, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 45 (Transfers on the basis of an adequacy decision), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_45> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Commission shall, on an ongoing basis, monitor developments in third countries and international organisations that could affect the functioning of decisions adopted pursuant to paragraph 3 of this Article and decisions adopted on the basis of Article 25(6) of Directive 95/46/EC."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 45, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 45 (Transfers on the basis of an adequacy decision), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_45> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Commission shall, where available information reveals, in particular following the review referred to in paragraph 3 of this Article, that a third country, a territory or one or more specified sectors within a third country, or an international organisation no longer ensures an adequate level of protection within the meaning of paragraph 2 of this Article, to the extent necessary, repeal, amend or suspend the decision referred to in paragraph 3 of this Article by means of implementing acts without retro-active effect. Those implementing acts shall be adopted in accordance with the examination procedure referred to in Article 93(2)."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 45, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 45 (Transfers on the basis of an adequacy decision), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_45> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45/Point_text_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "On duly justified imperative grounds of urgency, the Commission shall adopt immediately applicable implementing acts in accordance with the procedure referred to in Article 93(3)."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 45, point text_6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 45 (Transfers on the basis of an adequacy decision), point text_6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_45> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Commission shall enter into consultations with the third country or international organisation with a view to remedying the situation giving rise to the decision made pursuant to paragraph 5."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 45, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 45 (Transfers on the basis of an adequacy decision), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_45> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45/Point_7>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "A decision pursuant to paragraph 5 of this Article is without prejudice to transfers of personal data to the third country, a territory or one or more specified sectors within that third country, or the international organisation in question pursuant to Articles 46 to 49."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 45, point 7"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 45 (Transfers on the basis of an adequacy decision), point 7"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_45> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45/Point_8>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Commission shall publish in the Official Journal of the European Union and on its website a list of the third countries, territories and specified sectors within a third country and international organisations for which it has decided that an adequate level of protection is or is no longer ensured."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 45, point 8"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 45 (Transfers on the basis of an adequacy decision), point 8"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_45> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45/Point_9>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Decisions adopted by the Commission on the basis of Article 25(6) of Directive 95/46/EC shall remain in force until amended, replaced or repealed by a Commission Decision adopted in accordance with paragraph 3 or 5 of this Article."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 45, point 9"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 45 (Transfers on the basis of an adequacy decision), point 9"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_45>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_45> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "In the absence of a decision pursuant to Article 45(3), a controller or processor may transfer personal data to a third country or an international organisation only if the controller or processor has provided appropriate safeguards, and on condition that enforceable data subject rights and effective legal remedies for data subjects are available."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 46, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 46 (Transfers subject to appropriate safeguards), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_46> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The appropriate safeguards referred to in paragraph 1 may be provided for, without requiring any specific authorisation from a supervisory authority, by:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 46, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 46 (Transfers subject to appropriate safeguards), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_46> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46/Point_2a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "a legally binding and enforceable instrument between public authorities or bodies;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 46, point 2a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 46 (Transfers subject to appropriate safeguards), point 2a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_46> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46/Point_2b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "binding corporate rules in accordance with Article 47;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 46, point 2b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 46 (Transfers subject to appropriate safeguards), point 2b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_46> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46/Point_2c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "standard data protection clauses adopted by the Commission in accordance with the examination procedure referred to in Article 93(2);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 46, point 2c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 46 (Transfers subject to appropriate safeguards), point 2c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_46> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46/Point_2d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "standard data protection clauses adopted by a supervisory authority and approved by the Commission pursuant to the examination procedure referred to in Article 93(2);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 46, point 2d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 46 (Transfers subject to appropriate safeguards), point 2d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_46> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46/Point_2e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "an approved code of conduct pursuant to Article 40 together with binding and enforceable commitments of the controller or processor in the third country to apply the appropriate safeguards, including as regards data subjects' rights; or"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 46, point 2e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 46 (Transfers subject to appropriate safeguards), point 2e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_46> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46/Point_2f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "an approved certification mechanism pursuant to Article 42 together with binding and enforceable commitments of the controller or processor in the third country to apply the appropriate safeguards, including as regards data subjects' rights."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 46, point 2f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 46 (Transfers subject to appropriate safeguards), point 2f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_46> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Subject to the authorisation from the competent supervisory authority, the appropriate safeguards referred to in paragraph 1 may also be provided for, in particular, by:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 46, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 46 (Transfers subject to appropriate safeguards), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_46> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46/Point_3a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "contractual clauses between the controller or processor and the controller, processor or the recipient of the personal data in the third country or international organisation; or"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 46, point 3a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 46 (Transfers subject to appropriate safeguards), point 3a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_46> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46/Point_3b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "provisions to be inserted into administrative arrangements between public authorities or bodies which include enforceable and effective data subject rights."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 46, point 3b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 46 (Transfers subject to appropriate safeguards), point 3b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_46> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The supervisory authority shall apply the consistency mechanism referred to in Article 63 in the cases referred to in paragraph 3 of this Article."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 46, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 46 (Transfers subject to appropriate safeguards), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_46> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Authorisations by a Member State or supervisory authority on the basis of Article 26(2) of Directive 95/46/EC shall remain valid until amended, replaced or repealed, if necessary, by that supervisory authority. Decisions adopted by the Commission on the basis of Article 26(4) of Directive 95/46/EC shall remain in force until amended, replaced or repealed, if necessary, by a Commission Decision adopted in accordance with paragraph 2 of this Article."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 46, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 46 (Transfers subject to appropriate safeguards), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_46>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_46> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The competent supervisory authority shall approve binding corporate rules in accordance with the consistency mechanism set out in Article 63, provided that they:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 47, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 47 (Binding corporate rules), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_47> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47/Point_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "are legally binding and apply to and are enforced by every member concerned of the group of undertakings, or group of enterprises engaged in a joint economic activity, including their employees;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 47, point 1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 47 (Binding corporate rules), point 1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_47> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47/Point_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "expressly confer enforceable rights on data subjects with regard to the processing of their personal data; and"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 47, point 1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 47 (Binding corporate rules), point 1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_47> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47/Point_1c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "fulfil the requirements laid down in paragraph 2."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 47, point 1c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 47 (Binding corporate rules), point 1c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_47> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The binding corporate rules referred to in paragraph 1 shall specify at least:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 47, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 47 (Binding corporate rules), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_47> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47/Point_2a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the structure and contact details of the group of undertakings, or group of enterprises engaged in a joint economic activity and of each of its members;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 47, point 2a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 47 (Binding corporate rules), point 2a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_47> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47/Point_2b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the data transfers or set of transfers, including the categories of personal data, the type of processing and its purposes, the type of data subjects affected and the identification of the third country or countries in question;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 47, point 2b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 47 (Binding corporate rules), point 2b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_47> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47/Point_2c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "their legally binding nature, both internally and externally;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 47, point 2c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 47 (Binding corporate rules), point 2c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_47> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47/Point_2d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the application of the general data protection principles, in particular purpose limitation, data minimisation, limited storage periods, data quality, data protection by design and by default, legal basis for processing, processing of special categories of personal data, measures to ensure data security, and the requirements in respect of onward transfers to bodies not bound by the binding corporate rules;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 47, point 2d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 47 (Binding corporate rules), point 2d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_47> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47/Point_2e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the rights of data subjects in regard to processing and the means to exercise those rights, including the right not to be subject to decisions based solely on automated processing, including profiling in accordance with Article 22, the right to lodge a complaint with the competent supervisory authority and before the competent courts of the Member States in accordance with Article 79, and to obtain redress and, where appropriate, compensation for a breach of the binding corporate rules;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 47, point 2e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 47 (Binding corporate rules), point 2e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_47> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47/Point_2f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the acceptance by the controller or processor established on the territory of a Member State of liability for any breaches of the binding corporate rules by any member concerned not established in the Union; the controller or the processor shall be exempt from that liability, in whole or in part, only if it proves that that member is not responsible for the event giving rise to the damage;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 47, point 2f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 47 (Binding corporate rules), point 2f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_47> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47/Point_2g>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "how the information on the binding corporate rules, in particular on the provisions referred to in points (d), (e) and (f) of this paragraph is provided to the data subjects in addition to Articles 13 and 14;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 47, point 2g"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 47 (Binding corporate rules), point 2g"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_47> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47/Point_2h>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the tasks of any data protection officer designated in accordance with Article 37 or any other person or entity in charge of the monitoring compliance with the binding corporate rules within the group of undertakings, or group of enterprises engaged in a joint economic activity, as well as monitoring training and complaint-handling;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 47, point 2h"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 47 (Binding corporate rules), point 2h"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_47> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47/Point_2i>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the complaint procedures;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 47, point 2i"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 47 (Binding corporate rules), point 2i"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_47> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47/Point_2j>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the mechanisms within the group of undertakings, or group of enterprises engaged in a joint economic activity for ensuring the verification of compliance with the binding corporate rules. Such mechanisms shall include data protection audits and methods for ensuring corrective actions to protect the rights of the data subject. Results of such verification should be communicated to the person or entity referred to in point (h) and to the board of the controlling undertaking of a group of undertakings, or of the group of enterprises engaged in a joint economic activity, and should be available upon request to the competent supervisory authority;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 47, point 2j"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 47 (Binding corporate rules), point 2j"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_47> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47/Point_2k>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the mechanisms for reporting and recording changes to the rules and reporting those changes to the supervisory authority;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 47, point 2k"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 47 (Binding corporate rules), point 2k"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_47> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47/Point_2l>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the cooperation mechanism with the supervisory authority to ensure compliance by any member of the group of undertakings, or group of enterprises engaged in a joint economic activity, in particular by making available to the supervisory authority the results of verifications of the measures referred to in point (j);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 47, point 2l"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 47 (Binding corporate rules), point 2l"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_47> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47/Point_2m>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the mechanisms for reporting to the competent supervisory authority any legal requirements to which a member of the group of undertakings, or group of enterprises engaged in a joint economic activity is subject in a third country which are likely to have a substantial adverse effect on the guarantees provided by the binding corporate rules; and"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 47, point 2m"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 47 (Binding corporate rules), point 2m"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_47> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47/Point_2n>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the appropriate data protection training to personnel having permanent or regular access to personal data."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 47, point 2n"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 47 (Binding corporate rules), point 2n"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_47> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Commission may specify the format and procedures for the exchange of information between controllers, processors and supervisory authorities for binding corporate rules within the meaning of this Article. Those implementing acts shall be adopted in accordance with the examination procedure set out in Article 93(2)."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 47, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 47 (Binding corporate rules), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_47>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_47> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_48/Point_text_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Any judgment of a court or tribunal and any decision of an administrative authority of a third country requiring a controller or processor to transfer or disclose personal data may only be recognised or enforceable in any manner if based on an international agreement, such as a mutual legal assistance treaty, in force between the requesting third country and the Union or a Member State, without prejudice to other grounds for transfer pursuant to this Chapter."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 48, point text_1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 48 (Transfers or disclosures not authorised by Union law), point text_1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_48>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_48> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "In the absence of an adequacy decision pursuant to Article 45(3), or of appropriate safeguards pursuant to Article 46, including binding corporate rules, a transfer or a set of transfers of personal data to a third country or an international organisation shall take place only on one of the following conditions:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 49, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 49 (Derogations for specific situations), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_49> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49/Point_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the data subject has explicitly consented to the proposed transfer, after having been informed of the possible risks of such transfers for the data subject due to the absence of an adequacy decision and appropriate safeguards;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 49, point 1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 49 (Derogations for specific situations), point 1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_49> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49/Point_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the transfer is necessary for the performance of a contract between the data subject and the controller or the implementation of pre-contractual measures taken at the data subject's request;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 49, point 1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 49 (Derogations for specific situations), point 1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_49> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49/Point_1c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the transfer is necessary for the conclusion or performance of a contract concluded in the interest of the data subject between the controller and another natural or legal person;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 49, point 1c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 49 (Derogations for specific situations), point 1c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_49> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49/Point_1d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the transfer is necessary for important reasons of public interest;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 49, point 1d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 49 (Derogations for specific situations), point 1d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_49> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49/Point_1e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the transfer is necessary for the establishment, exercise or defence of legal claims;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 49, point 1e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 49 (Derogations for specific situations), point 1e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_49> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49/Point_1f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the transfer is necessary in order to protect the vital interests of the data subject or of other persons, where the data subject is physically or legally incapable of giving consent;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 49, point 1f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 49 (Derogations for specific situations), point 1f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_49> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49/Point_1g>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the transfer is made from a register which according to Union or Member State law is intended to provide information to the public and which is open to consultation either by the public in general or by any person who can demonstrate a legitimate interest, but only to the extent that the conditions laid down by Union or Member State law for consultation are fulfilled in the particular case."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 49, point 1g"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 49 (Derogations for specific situations), point 1g"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_49> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49/Point_text_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where a transfer could not be based on a provision in Article 45 or 46, including the provisions on binding corporate rules, and none of the derogations for a specific situation referred to in the first subparagraph of this paragraph is applicable, a transfer to a third country or an international organisation may take place only if the transfer is not repetitive, concerns only a limited number of data subjects, is necessary for the purposes of compelling legitimate interests pursued by the controller which are not overridden by the interests or rights and freedoms of the data subject, and the controller has assessed all the circumstances surrounding the data transfer and has on the basis of that assessment provided suitable safeguards with regard to the protection of personal data. The controller shall inform the supervisory authority of the transfer. The controller shall, in addition to providing the information referred to in Articles 13 and 14, inform the data subject of the transfer and on the compelling legitimate interests pursued."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 49, point text_2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 49 (Derogations for specific situations), point text_2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_49> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "A transfer pursuant to point (g) of the first subparagraph of paragraph 1 shall not involve the entirety of the personal data or entire categories of the personal data contained in the register. Where the register is intended for consultation by persons having a legitimate interest, the transfer shall be made only at the request of those persons or if they are to be the recipients."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 49, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 49 (Derogations for specific situations), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_49> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Points (a), (b) and (c) of the first subparagraph of paragraph 1 and the second subparagraph thereof shall not apply to activities carried out by public authorities in the exercise of their public powers."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 49, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 49 (Derogations for specific situations), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_49> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The public interest referred to in point (d) of the first subparagraph of paragraph 1 shall be recognised in Union law or in the law of the Member State to which the controller is subject."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 49, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 49 (Derogations for specific situations), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_49> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "In the absence of an adequacy decision, Union or Member State law may, for important reasons of public interest, expressly set limits to the transfer of specific categories of personal data to a third country or an international organisation. Member States shall notify such provisions to the Commission."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 49, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 49 (Derogations for specific situations), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_49> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The controller or processor shall document the assessment as well as the suitable safeguards referred to in the second subparagraph of paragraph 1 of this Article in the records referred to in Article 30."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 49, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 49 (Derogations for specific situations), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_49>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_49> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_50/Point_text_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "In relation to third countries and international organisations, the Commission and supervisory authorities shall take appropriate steps to:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 50, point text_1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 50 (International cooperation for the protection of personal data), point text_1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_50>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_50> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_50/Point_text_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "develop international cooperation mechanisms to facilitate the effective enforcement of legislation for the protection of personal data;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 50, point text_1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 50 (International cooperation for the protection of personal data), point text_1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_50>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_50> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_50/Point_text_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "provide international mutual assistance in the enforcement of legislation for the protection of personal data, including through notification, complaint referral, investigative assistance and information exchange, subject to appropriate safeguards for the protection of personal data and other fundamental rights and freedoms;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 50, point text_1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 50 (International cooperation for the protection of personal data), point text_1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_50>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_50> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_50/Point_text_1c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "engage relevant stakeholders in discussion and activities aimed at furthering international cooperation in the enforcement of legislation for the protection of personal data;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 50, point text_1c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 50 (International cooperation for the protection of personal data), point text_1c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_50>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_50> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_50/Point_text_1d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "promote the exchange and documentation of personal data protection legislation and practice, including on jurisdictional conflicts with third countries."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter V, article 50, point text_1d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter V (Transfers of personal data to third countries or international organisations), article 50 (International cooperation for the protection of personal data), point text_1d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_V/Article_50>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_v_article_50> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_51/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each Member State shall provide for one or more independent public authorities to be responsible for monitoring the application of this Regulation, in order to protect the fundamental rights and freedoms of natural persons in relation to processing and to facilitate the free flow of personal data within the Union (‘supervisory authority’)."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 51, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 51 (Supervisory authority), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_51>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_51> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_51/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each supervisory authority shall contribute to the consistent application of this Regulation throughout the Union. For that purpose, the supervisory authorities shall cooperate with each other and the Commission in accordance with Chapter VII."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 51, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 51 (Supervisory authority), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_51>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_51> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_51/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where more than one supervisory authority is established in a Member State, that Member State shall designate the supervisory authority which is to represent those authorities in the Board and shall set out the mechanism to ensure compliance by the other authorities with the rules relating to the consistency mechanism referred to in Article 63."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 51, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 51 (Supervisory authority), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_51>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_51> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_51/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each Member State shall notify to the Commission the provisions of its law which it adopts pursuant to this Chapter, by 25 May 2018 and, without delay, any subsequent amendment affecting them."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 51, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 51 (Supervisory authority), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_51>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_51> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_52/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each supervisory authority shall act with complete independence in performing its tasks and exercising its powers in accordance with this Regulation."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 52, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 52 (Independence), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_52>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_52> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_52/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The member or members of each supervisory authority shall, in the performance of their tasks and exercise of their powers in accordance with this Regulation, remain free from external influence, whether direct or indirect, and shall neither seek nor take instructions from anybody."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 52, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 52 (Independence), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_52>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_52> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_52/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Member or members of each supervisory authority shall refrain from any action incompatible with their duties and shall not, during their term of office, engage in any incompatible occupation, whether gainful or not."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 52, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 52 (Independence), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_52>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_52> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_52/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each Member State shall ensure that each supervisory authority is provided with the human, technical and financial resources, premises and infrastructure necessary for the effective performance of its tasks and exercise of its powers, including those to be carried out in the context of mutual assistance, cooperation and participation in the Board."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 52, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 52 (Independence), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_52>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_52> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_52/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each Member State shall ensure that each supervisory authority chooses and has its own staff which shall be subject to the exclusive direction of the member or members of the supervisory authority concerned."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 52, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 52 (Independence), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_52>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_52> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_52/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each Member State shall ensure that each supervisory authority is subject to financial control which does not affect its independence and that it has separate, public annual budgets, which may be part of the overall state or national budget."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 52, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 52 (Independence), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_52>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_52> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_53/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Member States shall provide for each member of their supervisory authorities to be appointed by means of a transparent procedure by:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 53, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 53 (General conditions for the members of the supervisory authority), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_53>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_53> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_53/Point_1subpoint_1>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "their parliament;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 53, point 1subpoint_1"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 53 (General conditions for the members of the supervisory authority), point 1subpoint_1"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_53>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_53> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_53/Point_1subpoint_2>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "their government;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 53, point 1subpoint_2"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 53 (General conditions for the members of the supervisory authority), point 1subpoint_2"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_53>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_53> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_53/Point_1subpoint_3>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "their head of State; or"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 53, point 1subpoint_3"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 53 (General conditions for the members of the supervisory authority), point 1subpoint_3"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_53>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_53> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_53/Point_1subpoint_4>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "an independent body entrusted with the appointment under Member State law."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 53, point 1subpoint_4"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 53 (General conditions for the members of the supervisory authority), point 1subpoint_4"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_53>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_53> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_53/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each member shall have the qualifications, experience and skills, in particular in the area of the protection of personal data, required to perform its duties and exercise its powers."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 53, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 53 (General conditions for the members of the supervisory authority), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_53>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_53> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_53/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The duties of a member shall end in the event of the expiry of the term of office, resignation or compulsory retirement, in accordance with the law of the Member State concerned."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 53, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 53 (General conditions for the members of the supervisory authority), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_53>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_53> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_53/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "A member shall be dismissed only in cases of serious misconduct or if the member no longer fulfils the conditions required for the performance of the duties."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 53, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 53 (General conditions for the members of the supervisory authority), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_53>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_53> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_54/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each Member State shall provide by law for all of the following:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 54, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 54 (Rules on the establishment of the supervisory authority), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_54>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_54> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_54/Point_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the establishment of each supervisory authority;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 54, point 1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 54 (Rules on the establishment of the supervisory authority), point 1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_54>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_54> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_54/Point_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the qualifications and eligibility conditions required to be appointed as member of each supervisory authority;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 54, point 1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 54 (Rules on the establishment of the supervisory authority), point 1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_54>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_54> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_54/Point_1c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the rules and procedures for the appointment of the member or members of each supervisory authority;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 54, point 1c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 54 (Rules on the establishment of the supervisory authority), point 1c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_54>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_54> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_54/Point_1d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the duration of the term of the member or members of each supervisory authority of no less than four years, except for the first appointment after 24 May 2016, part of which may take place for a shorter period where that is necessary to protect the independence of the supervisory authority by means of a staggered appointment procedure;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 54, point 1d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 54 (Rules on the establishment of the supervisory authority), point 1d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_54>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_54> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_54/Point_1e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "whether and, if so, for how many terms the member or members of each supervisory authority is eligible for reappointment;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 54, point 1e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 54 (Rules on the establishment of the supervisory authority), point 1e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_54>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_54> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_54/Point_1f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the conditions governing the obligations of the member or members and staff of each supervisory authority, prohibitions on actions, occupations and benefits incompatible therewith during and after the term of office and rules governing the cessation of employment."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 54, point 1f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 54 (Rules on the establishment of the supervisory authority), point 1f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_54>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_54> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_54/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The member or members and the staff of each supervisory authority shall, in accordance with Union or Member State law, be subject to a duty of professional secrecy both during and after their term of office, with regard to any confidential information which has come to their knowledge in the course of the performance of their tasks or exercise of their powers. During their term of office, that duty of professional secrecy shall in particular apply to reporting by natural persons of infringements of this Regulation."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 54, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 54 (Rules on the establishment of the supervisory authority), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_54>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_54> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_55/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each supervisory authority shall be competent for the performance of the tasks assigned to and the exercise of the powers conferred on it in accordance with this Regulation on the territory of its own Member State."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 55, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 55 (Competence), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_55>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_55> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_55/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where processing is carried out by public authorities or private bodies acting on the basis of point (c) or (e) of Article 6(1), the supervisory authority of the Member State concerned shall be competent. In such cases Article 56 does not apply."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 55, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 55 (Competence), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_55>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_55> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_55/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Supervisory authorities shall not be competent to supervise processing operations of courts acting in their judicial capacity."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 55, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 55 (Competence), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_55>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_55> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_56/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Without prejudice to Article 55, the supervisory authority of the main establishment or of the single establishment of the controller or processor shall be competent to act as lead supervisory authority for the cross-border processing carried out by that controller or processor in accordance with the procedure provided in Article 60."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 56, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 56 (Competence of the lead supervisory authority), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_56>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_56> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_56/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "By derogation from paragraph 1, each supervisory authority shall be competent to handle a complaint lodged with it or a possible infringement of this Regulation, if the subject matter relates only to an establishment in its Member State or substantially affects data subjects only in its Member State."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 56, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 56 (Competence of the lead supervisory authority), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_56>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_56> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_56/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "In the cases referred to in paragraph 2 of this Article, the supervisory authority shall inform the lead supervisory authority without delay on that matter. Within a period of three weeks after being informed the lead supervisory authority shall decide whether or not it will handle the case in accordance with the procedure provided in Article 60, taking into account whether or not there is an establishment of the controller or processor in the Member State of which the supervisory authority informed it."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 56, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 56 (Competence of the lead supervisory authority), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_56>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_56> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_56/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where the lead supervisory authority decides to handle the case, the procedure provided in Article 60 shall apply. The supervisory authority which informed the lead supervisory authority may submit to the lead supervisory authority a draft for a decision. The lead supervisory authority shall take utmost account of that draft when preparing the draft decision referred to in Article 60(3)."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 56, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 56 (Competence of the lead supervisory authority), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_56>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_56> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_56/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where the lead supervisory authority decides not to handle the case, the supervisory authority which informed the lead supervisory authority shall handle it according to Articles 61 and 62."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 56, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 56 (Competence of the lead supervisory authority), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_56>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_56> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_56/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The lead supervisory authority shall be the sole interlocutor of the controller or processor for the cross-border processing carried out by that controller or processor."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 56, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 56 (Competence of the lead supervisory authority), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_56>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_56> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Without prejudice to other tasks set out under this Regulation, each supervisory authority shall on its territory:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "monitor and enforce the application of this Regulation;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "promote public awareness and understanding of the risks, rules, safeguards and rights in relation to processing. Activities addressed specifically to children shall receive specific attention;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "advise, in accordance with Member State law, the national parliament, the government, and other institutions and bodies on legislative and administrative measures relating to the protection of natural persons' rights and freedoms with regard to processing;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "promote the awareness of controllers and processors of their obligations under this Regulation;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "upon request, provide information to any data subject concerning the exercise of their rights under this Regulation and, if appropriate, cooperate with the supervisory authorities in other Member States to that end;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "handle complaints lodged by a data subject, or by a body, organisation or association in accordance with Article 80, and investigate, to the extent appropriate, the subject matter of the complaint and inform the complainant of the progress and the outcome of the investigation within a reasonable period, in particular if further investigation or coordination with another supervisory authority is necessary;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1g>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "cooperate with, including sharing information and provide mutual assistance to, other supervisory authorities with a view to ensuring the consistency of application and enforcement of this Regulation;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1g"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1g"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1h>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "conduct investigations on the application of this Regulation, including on the basis of information received from another supervisory authority or other public authority;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1h"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1h"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1i>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "monitor relevant developments, insofar as they have an impact on the protection of personal data, in particular the development of information and communication technologies and commercial practices;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1i"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1i"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1j>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "adopt standard contractual clauses referred to in Article 28(8) and in point (d) of Article 46(2);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1j"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1j"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1k>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "establish and maintain a list in relation to the requirement for data protection impact assessment pursuant to Article 35(4);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1k"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1k"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1l>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "give advice on the processing operations referred to in Article 36(2);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1l"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1l"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1m>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "encourage the drawing up of codes of conduct pursuant to Article 40(1) and provide an opinion and approve such codes of conduct which provide sufficient safeguards, pursuant to Article 40(5);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1m"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1m"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1n>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "encourage the establishment of data protection certification mechanisms and of data protection seals and marks pursuant to Article 42(1), and approve the criteria of certification pursuant to Article 42(5);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1n"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1n"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1o>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "where applicable, carry out a periodic review of certifications issued in accordance with Article 42(7);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1o"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1o"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1p>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "draft and publish the criteria for accreditation of a body for monitoring codes of conduct pursuant to Article 41 and of a certification body pursuant to Article 43;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1p"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1p"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1q>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "conduct the accreditation of a body for monitoring codes of conduct pursuant to Article 41 and of a certification body pursuant to Article 43;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1q"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1q"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1r>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "authorise contractual clauses and provisions referred to in Article 46(3);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1r"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1r"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1s>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "approve binding corporate rules pursuant to Article 47;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1s"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1s"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1t>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "contribute to the activities of the Board;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1t"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1t"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1u>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "keep internal records of infringements of this Regulation and of measures taken in accordance with Article 58(2); and"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1u"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1u"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_1v>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "fulfil any other tasks related to the protection of personal data."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 1v"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 1v"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each supervisory authority shall facilitate the submission of complaints referred to in point (f) of paragraph 1 by measures such as a complaint submission form which can also be completed electronically, without excluding other means of communication."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The performance of the tasks of each supervisory authority shall be free of charge for the data subject and, where applicable, for the data protection officer."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where requests are manifestly unfounded or excessive, in particular because of their repetitive character, the supervisory authority may charge a reasonable fee based on administrative costs, or refuse to act on the request. The supervisory authority shall bear the burden of demonstrating the manifestly unfounded or excessive character of the request."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 57, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 57 (Tasks), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_57>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_57> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each supervisory authority shall have all of the following investigative powers:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to order the controller and the processor, and, where applicable, the controller's or the processor's representative to provide any information it requires for the performance of its tasks;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to carry out investigations in the form of data protection audits;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_1c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to carry out a review on certifications issued pursuant to Article 42(7);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 1c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 1c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_1d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to notify the controller or the processor of an alleged infringement of this Regulation;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 1d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 1d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_1e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to obtain, from the controller and the processor, access to all personal data and to all information necessary for the performance of its tasks;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 1e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 1e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_1f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to obtain access to any premises of the controller and the processor, including to any data processing equipment and means, in accordance with Union or Member State procedural law."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 1f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 1f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each supervisory authority shall have all of the following corrective powers:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_2a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to issue warnings to a controller or processor that intended processing operations are likely to infringe provisions of this Regulation;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 2a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 2a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_2b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to issue reprimands to a controller or a processor where processing operations have infringed provisions of this Regulation;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 2b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 2b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_2c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to order the controller or the processor to comply with the data subject's requests to exercise his or her rights pursuant to this Regulation;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 2c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 2c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_2d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to order the controller or processor to bring processing operations into compliance with the provisions of this Regulation, where appropriate, in a specified manner and within a specified period;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 2d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 2d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_2e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to order the controller to communicate a personal data breach to the data subject;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 2e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 2e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_2f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to impose a temporary or definitive limitation including a ban on processing;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 2f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 2f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_2g>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to order the rectification or erasure of personal data or restriction of processing pursuant to Articles 16, 17 and 18 and the notification of such actions to recipients to whom the personal data have been disclosed pursuant to Article 17(2) and Article 19;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 2g"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 2g"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_2h>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to withdraw a certification or to order the certification body to withdraw a certification issued pursuant to Articles 42 and 43, or to order the certification body not to issue certification if the requirements for the certification are not or are no longer met;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 2h"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 2h"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_2i>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to impose an administrative fine pursuant to Article 83, in addition to, or instead of measures referred to in this paragraph, depending on the circumstances of each individual case;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 2i"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 2i"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_2j>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to order the suspension of data flows to a recipient in a third country or to an international organisation."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 2j"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 2j"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each supervisory authority shall have all of the following authorisation and advisory powers:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_3a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to advise the controller in accordance with the prior consultation procedure referred to in Article 36;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 3a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 3a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_3b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to issue, on its own initiative or on request, opinions to the national parliament, the Member State government or, in accordance with Member State law, to other institutions and bodies as well as to the public on any issue related to the protection of personal data;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 3b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 3b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_3c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to authorise processing referred to in Article 36(5), if the law of the Member State requires such prior authorisation;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 3c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 3c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_3d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to issue an opinion and approve draft codes of conduct pursuant to Article 40(5);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 3d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 3d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_3e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to accredit certification bodies pursuant to Article 43;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 3e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 3e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_3f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to issue certifications and approve criteria of certification in accordance with Article 42(5);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 3f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 3f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_3g>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to adopt standard data protection clauses referred to in Article 28(8) and in point (d) of Article 46(2);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 3g"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 3g"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_3h>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to authorise contractual clauses referred to in point (a) of Article 46(3);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 3h"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 3h"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_3i>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to authorise administrative arrangements referred to in point (b) of Article 46(3);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 3i"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 3i"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_3j>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to approve binding corporate rules pursuant to Article 47."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 3j"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 3j"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The exercise of the powers conferred on the supervisory authority pursuant to this Article shall be subject to appropriate safeguards, including effective judicial remedy and due process, set out in Union and Member State law in accordance with the Charter."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each Member State shall provide by law that its supervisory authority shall have the power to bring infringements of this Regulation to the attention of the judicial authorities and where appropriate, to commence or engage otherwise in legal proceedings, in order to enforce the provisions of this Regulation."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each Member State may provide by law that its supervisory authority shall have additional powers to those referred to in paragraphs 1, 2 and 3. The exercise of those powers shall not impair the effective operation of Chapter VII."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 58, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 58 (Powers), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_58>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_58> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_59/Point_text_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each supervisory authority shall draw up an annual report on its activities, which may include a list of types of infringement notified and types of measures taken in accordance with Article 58(2). Those reports shall be transmitted to the national parliament, the government and other authorities as designated by Member State law. They shall be made available to the public, to the Commission and to the Board."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VI, article 59, point text_1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VI (Independent supervisory authorities), article 59 (Activity reports), point text_1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VI/Article_59>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vi_article_59> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The lead supervisory authority shall cooperate with the other supervisory authorities concerned in accordance with this Article in an endeavour to reach consensus. The lead supervisory authority and the supervisory authorities concerned shall exchange all relevant information with each other."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 60, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 60 (Cooperation between the lead supervisory authority and the other supervisory authorities concerned), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_60> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The lead supervisory authority may request at any time other supervisory authorities concerned to provide mutual assistance pursuant to Article 61 and may conduct joint operations pursuant to Article 62, in particular for carrying out investigations or for monitoring the implementation of a measure concerning a controller or processor established in another Member State."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 60, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 60 (Cooperation between the lead supervisory authority and the other supervisory authorities concerned), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_60> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The lead supervisory authority shall, without delay, communicate the relevant information on the matter to the other supervisory authorities concerned. It shall without delay submit a draft decision to the other supervisory authorities concerned for their opinion and take due account of their views."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 60, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 60 (Cooperation between the lead supervisory authority and the other supervisory authorities concerned), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_60> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where any of the other supervisory authorities concerned within a period of four weeks after having been consulted in accordance with paragraph 3 of this Article, expresses a relevant and reasoned objection to the draft decision, the lead supervisory authority shall, if it does not follow the relevant and reasoned objection or is of the opinion that the objection is not relevant or reasoned, submit the matter to the consistency mechanism referred to in Article 63."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 60, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 60 (Cooperation between the lead supervisory authority and the other supervisory authorities concerned), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_60> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where the lead supervisory authority intends to follow the relevant and reasoned objection made, it shall submit to the other supervisory authorities concerned a revised draft decision for their opinion. That revised draft decision shall be subject to the procedure referred to in paragraph 4 within a period of two weeks."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 60, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 60 (Cooperation between the lead supervisory authority and the other supervisory authorities concerned), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_60> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where none of the other supervisory authorities concerned has objected to the draft decision submitted by the lead supervisory authority within the period referred to in paragraphs 4 and 5, the lead supervisory authority and the supervisory authorities concerned shall be deemed to be in agreement with that draft decision and shall be bound by it."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 60, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 60 (Cooperation between the lead supervisory authority and the other supervisory authorities concerned), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_60> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60/Point_7>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The lead supervisory authority shall adopt and notify the decision to the main establishment or single establishment of the controller or processor, as the case may be and inform the other supervisory authorities concerned and the Board of the decision in question, including a summary of the relevant facts and grounds. The supervisory authority with which a complaint has been lodged shall inform the complainant on the decision."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 60, point 7"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 60 (Cooperation between the lead supervisory authority and the other supervisory authorities concerned), point 7"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_60> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60/Point_8>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "By derogation from paragraph 7, where a complaint is dismissed or rejected, the supervisory authority with which the complaint was lodged shall adopt the decision and notify it to the complainant and shall inform the controller thereof."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 60, point 8"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 60 (Cooperation between the lead supervisory authority and the other supervisory authorities concerned), point 8"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_60> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60/Point_9>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where the lead supervisory authority and the supervisory authorities concerned agree to dismiss or reject parts of a complaint and to act on other parts of that complaint, a separate decision shall be adopted for each of those parts of the matter. The lead supervisory authority shall adopt the decision for the part concerning actions in relation to the controller, shall notify it to the main establishment or single establishment of the controller or processor on the territory of its Member State and shall inform the complainant thereof, while the supervisory authority of the complainant shall adopt the decision for the part concerning dismissal or rejection of that complaint, and shall notify it to that complainant and shall inform the controller or processor thereof."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 60, point 9"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 60 (Cooperation between the lead supervisory authority and the other supervisory authorities concerned), point 9"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_60> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60/Point_10>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "After being notified of the decision of the lead supervisory authority pursuant to paragraphs 7 and 9, the controller or processor shall take the necessary measures to ensure compliance with the decision as regards processing activities in the context of all its establishments in the Union. The controller or processor shall notify the measures taken for complying with the decision to the lead supervisory authority, which shall inform the other supervisory authorities concerned."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 60, point 10"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 60 (Cooperation between the lead supervisory authority and the other supervisory authorities concerned), point 10"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_60> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60/Point_11>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where, in exceptional circumstances, a supervisory authority concerned has reasons to consider that there is an urgent need to act in order to protect the interests of data subjects, the urgency procedure referred to in Article 66 shall apply."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 60, point 11"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 60 (Cooperation between the lead supervisory authority and the other supervisory authorities concerned), point 11"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_60> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60/Point_12>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The lead supervisory authority and the other supervisory authorities concerned shall supply the information required under this Article to each other by electronic means, using a standardised format."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 60, point 12"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 60 (Cooperation between the lead supervisory authority and the other supervisory authorities concerned), point 12"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_60>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_60> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_61/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Supervisory authorities shall provide each other with relevant information and mutual assistance in order to implement and apply this Regulation in a consistent manner, and shall put in place measures for effective cooperation with one another. Mutual assistance shall cover, in particular, information requests and supervisory measures, such as requests to carry out prior authorisations and consultations, inspections and investigations."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 61, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 61 (Mutual assistance), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_61>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_61> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_61/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each supervisory authority shall take all appropriate measures required to reply to a request of another supervisory authority without undue delay and no later than one month after receiving the request. Such measures may include, in particular, the transmission of relevant information on the conduct of an investigation."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 61, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 61 (Mutual assistance), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_61>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_61> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_61/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Requests for assistance shall contain all the necessary information, including the purpose of and reasons for the request. Information exchanged shall be used only for the purpose for which it was requested."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 61, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 61 (Mutual assistance), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_61>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_61> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_61/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The requested supervisory authority shall not refuse to comply with the request unless:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 61, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 61 (Mutual assistance), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_61>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_61> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_61/Point_4a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "it is not competent for the subject-matter of the request or for the measures it is requested to execute; or"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 61, point 4a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 61 (Mutual assistance), point 4a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_61>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_61> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_61/Point_4b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "compliance with the request would infringe this Regulation or Union or Member State law to which the supervisory authority receiving the request is subject."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 61, point 4b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 61 (Mutual assistance), point 4b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_61>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_61> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_61/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The requested supervisory authority shall inform the requesting supervisory authority of the results or, as the case may be, of the progress of the measures taken in order to respond to the request. The requested supervisory authority shall provide reasons for any refusal to comply with a request pursuant to paragraph 4."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 61, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 61 (Mutual assistance), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_61>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_61> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_61/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Requested supervisory authorities shall, as a rule, supply the information requested by other supervisory authorities by electronic means, using a standardised format."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 61, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 61 (Mutual assistance), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_61>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_61> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_61/Point_7>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Requested supervisory authorities shall not charge a fee for any action taken by them pursuant to a request for mutual assistance. Supervisory authorities may agree on rules to indemnify each other for specific expenditure arising from the provision of mutual assistance in exceptional circumstances."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 61, point 7"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 61 (Mutual assistance), point 7"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_61>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_61> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_61/Point_8>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where a supervisory authority does not provide the information referred to in paragraph 5 of this Article within one month of receiving the request of another supervisory authority, the requesting supervisory authority may adopt a provisional measure on the territory of its Member State in accordance with Article 55(1). In that case, the urgent need to act under Article 66(1) shall be presumed to be met and require an urgent binding decision from the Board pursuant to Article 66(2)."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 61, point 8"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 61 (Mutual assistance), point 8"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_61>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_61> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_61/Point_9>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Commission may, by means of implementing acts, specify the format and procedures for mutual assistance referred to in this Article and the arrangements for the exchange of information by electronic means between supervisory authorities, and between supervisory authorities and the Board, in particular the standardised format referred to in paragraph 6 of this Article. Those implementing acts shall be adopted in accordance with the examination procedure referred to in Article 93(2)."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 61, point 9"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 61 (Mutual assistance), point 9"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_61>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_61> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_62/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The supervisory authorities shall, where appropriate, conduct joint operations including joint investigations and joint enforcement measures in which members or staff of the supervisory authorities of other Member States are involved."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 62, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 62 (Joint operations of supervisory authorities), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_62>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_62> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_62/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where the controller or processor has establishments in several Member States or where a significant number of data subjects in more than one Member State are likely to be substantially affected by processing operations, a supervisory authority of each of those Member States shall have the right to participate in joint operations. The supervisory authority which is competent pursuant to Article 56(1) or (4) shall invite the supervisory authority of each of those Member States to take part in the joint operations and shall respond without delay to the request of a supervisory authority to participate."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 62, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 62 (Joint operations of supervisory authorities), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_62>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_62> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_62/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "A supervisory authority may, in accordance with Member State law, and with the seconding supervisory authority's authorisation, confer powers, including investigative powers on the seconding supervisory authority's members or staff involved in joint operations or, in so far as the law of the Member State of the host supervisory authority permits, allow the seconding supervisory authority's members or staff to exercise their investigative powers in accordance with the law of the Member State of the seconding supervisory authority. Such investigative powers may be exercised only under the guidance and in the presence of members or staff of the host supervisory authority. The seconding supervisory authority's members or staff shall be subject to the Member State law of the host supervisory authority."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 62, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 62 (Joint operations of supervisory authorities), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_62>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_62> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_62/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where, in accordance with paragraph 1, staff of a seconding supervisory authority operate in another Member State, the Member State of the host supervisory authority shall assume responsibility for their actions, including liability, for any damage caused by them during their operations, in accordance with the law of the Member State in whose territory they are operating."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 62, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 62 (Joint operations of supervisory authorities), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_62>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_62> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_62/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Member State in whose territory the damage was caused shall make good such damage under the conditions applicable to damage caused by its own staff. The Member State of the seconding supervisory authority whose staff has caused damage to any person in the territory of another Member State shall reimburse that other Member State in full any sums it has paid to the persons entitled on their behalf."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 62, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 62 (Joint operations of supervisory authorities), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_62>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_62> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_62/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Without prejudice to the exercise of its rights vis-à-vis third parties and with the exception of paragraph 5, each Member State shall refrain, in the case provided for in paragraph 1, from requesting reimbursement from another Member State in relation to damage referred to in paragraph 4."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 62, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 62 (Joint operations of supervisory authorities), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_62>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_62> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_62/Point_7>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where a joint operation is intended and a supervisory authority does not, within one month, comply with the obligation laid down in the second sentence of paragraph 2 of this Article, the other supervisory authorities may adopt a provisional measure on the territory of its Member State in accordance with Article 55. In that case, the urgent need to act under Article 66(1) shall be presumed to be met and require an opinion or an urgent binding decision from the Board pursuant to Article 66(2)."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 62, point 7"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 62 (Joint operations of supervisory authorities), point 7"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_62>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_62> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_63/Point_text_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "In order to contribute to the consistent application of this Regulation throughout the Union, the supervisory authorities shall cooperate with each other and, where relevant, with the Commission, through the consistency mechanism as set out in this Section."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 63, point text_1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 63 (Consistency mechanism), point text_1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_63>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_63> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Board shall issue an opinion where a competent supervisory authority intends to adopt any of the measures below. To that end, the competent supervisory authority shall communicate the draft decision to the Board, when it:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 64, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 64 (Opinion of the Board), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_64> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64/Point_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "aims to adopt a list of the processing operations subject to the requirement for a data protection impact assessment pursuant to Article 35(4);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 64, point 1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 64 (Opinion of the Board), point 1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_64> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64/Point_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "concerns a matter pursuant to Article 40(7) whether a draft code of conduct or an amendment or extension to a code of conduct complies with this Regulation;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 64, point 1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 64 (Opinion of the Board), point 1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_64> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64/Point_1c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "aims to approve the criteria for accreditation of a body pursuant to Article 41(3) or a certification body pursuant to Article 43(3);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 64, point 1c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 64 (Opinion of the Board), point 1c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_64> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64/Point_1d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "aims to determine standard data protection clauses referred to in point (d) of Article 46(2) and in Article 28(8);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 64, point 1d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 64 (Opinion of the Board), point 1d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_64> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64/Point_1e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "aims to authorise contractual clauses referred to in point (a) of Article 46(3); or"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 64, point 1e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 64 (Opinion of the Board), point 1e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_64> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64/Point_1f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "aims to approve binding corporate rules within the meaning of Article 47."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 64, point 1f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 64 (Opinion of the Board), point 1f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_64> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Any supervisory authority, the Chair of the Board or the Commission may request that any matter of general application or producing effects in more than one Member State be examined by the Board with a view to obtaining an opinion, in particular where a competent supervisory authority does not comply with the obligations for mutual assistance in accordance with Article 61 or for joint operations in accordance with Article 62."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 64, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 64 (Opinion of the Board), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_64> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "In the cases referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2, the Board shall issue an opinion on the matter submitted to it provided that it has not already issued an opinion on the same matter. That opinion shall be adopted within eight weeks by simple majority of the members of the Board. That period may be extended by a further six weeks, taking into account the complexity of the subject matter. Regarding the draft decision referred to in paragraph 1 circulated to the members of the Board in accordance with paragraph 5, a member which has not objected within a reasonable period indicated by the Chair, shall be deemed to be in agreement with the draft decision."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 64, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 64 (Opinion of the Board), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_64> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Supervisory authorities and the Commission shall, without undue delay, communicate by electronic means to the Board, using a standardised format any relevant information, including as the case may be a summary of the facts, the draft decision, the grounds which make the enactment of such measure necessary, and the views of other supervisory authorities concerned."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 64, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 64 (Opinion of the Board), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_64> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Chair of the Board shall, without undue, delay inform by electronic means:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 64, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 64 (Opinion of the Board), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_64> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64/Point_5a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the members of the Board and the Commission of any relevant information which has been communicated to it using a standardised format. The secretariat of the Board shall, where necessary, provide translations of relevant information; and"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 64, point 5a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 64 (Opinion of the Board), point 5a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_64> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64/Point_5b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the supervisory authority referred to, as the case may be, in paragraphs 1 and 2, and the Commission of the opinion and make it public."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 64, point 5b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 64 (Opinion of the Board), point 5b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_64> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The competent supervisory authority shall not adopt its draft decision referred to in paragraph 1 within the period referred to in paragraph 3."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 64, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 64 (Opinion of the Board), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_64> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64/Point_7>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The supervisory authority referred to in paragraph 1 shall take utmost account of the opinion of the Board and shall, within two weeks after receiving the opinion, communicate to the Chair of the Board by electronic means whether it will maintain or amend its draft decision and, if any, the amended draft decision, using a standardised format."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 64, point 7"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 64 (Opinion of the Board), point 7"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_64> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64/Point_8>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where the supervisory authority concerned informs the Chair of the Board within the period referred to in paragraph 7 of this Article that it does not intend to follow the opinion of the Board, in whole or in part, providing the relevant grounds, Article 65(1) shall apply."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 64, point 8"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 64 (Opinion of the Board), point 8"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_64>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_64> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_65/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "In order to ensure the correct and consistent application of this Regulation in individual cases, the Board shall adopt a binding decision in the following cases:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 65, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 65 (Dispute resolution by the Board), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_65>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_65> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_65/Point_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "where, in a case referred to in Article 60(4), a supervisory authority concerned has raised a relevant and reasoned objection to a draft decision of the lead authority or the lead authority has rejected such an objection as being not relevant or reasoned. The binding decision shall concern all the matters which are the subject of the relevant and reasoned objection, in particular whether there is an infringement of this Regulation;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 65, point 1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 65 (Dispute resolution by the Board), point 1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_65>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_65> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_65/Point_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "where there are conflicting views on which of the supervisory authorities concerned is competent for the main establishment;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 65, point 1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 65 (Dispute resolution by the Board), point 1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_65>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_65> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_65/Point_1c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "where a competent supervisory authority does not request the opinion of the Board in the cases referred to in Article 64(1), or does not follow the opinion of the Board issued under Article 64. In that case, any supervisory authority concerned or the Commission may communicate the matter to the Board."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 65, point 1c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 65 (Dispute resolution by the Board), point 1c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_65>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_65> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_65/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The decision referred to in paragraph 1 shall be adopted within one month from the referral of the subject-matter by a two-thirds majority of the members of the Board. That period may be extended by a further month on account of the complexity of the subject-matter. The decision referred to in paragraph 1 shall be reasoned and addressed to the lead supervisory authority and all the supervisory authorities concerned and binding on them."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 65, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 65 (Dispute resolution by the Board), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_65>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_65> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_65/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where the Board has been unable to adopt a decision within the periods referred to in paragraph 2, it shall adopt its decision within two weeks following the expiration of the second month referred to in paragraph 2 by a simple majority of the members of the Board. Where the members of the Board are split, the decision shall by adopted by the vote of its Chair."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 65, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 65 (Dispute resolution by the Board), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_65>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_65> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_65/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The supervisory authorities concerned shall not adopt a decision on the subject matter submitted to the Board under paragraph 1 during the periods referred to in paragraphs 2 and 3."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 65, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 65 (Dispute resolution by the Board), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_65>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_65> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_65/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Chair of the Board shall notify, without undue delay, the decision referred to in paragraph 1 to the supervisory authorities concerned. It shall inform the Commission thereof. The decision shall be published on the website of the Board without delay after the supervisory authority has notified the final decision referred to in paragraph 6."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 65, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 65 (Dispute resolution by the Board), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_65>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_65> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_65/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The lead supervisory authority or, as the case may be, the supervisory authority with which the complaint has been lodged shall adopt its final decision on the basis of the decision referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article, without undue delay and at the latest by one month after the Board has notified its decision. The lead supervisory authority or, as the case may be, the supervisory authority with which the complaint has been lodged, shall inform the Board of the date when its final decision is notified respectively to the controller or the processor and to the data subject. The final decision of the supervisory authorities concerned shall be adopted under the terms of Article 60(7), (8) and (9). The final decision shall refer to the decision referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article and shall specify that the decision referred to in that paragraph will be published on the website of the Board in accordance with paragraph 5 of this Article. The final decision shall attach the decision referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 65, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 65 (Dispute resolution by the Board), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_65>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_65> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_66/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "In exceptional circumstances, where a supervisory authority concerned considers that there is an urgent need to act in order to protect the rights and freedoms of data subjects, it may, by way of derogation from the consistency mechanism referred to in Articles 63, 64 and 65 or the procedure referred to in Article 60, immediately adopt provisional measures intended to produce legal effects on its own territory with a specified period of validity which shall not exceed three months. The supervisory authority shall, without delay, communicate those measures and the reasons for adopting them to the other supervisory authorities concerned, to the Board and to the Commission."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 66, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 66 (Urgency procedure), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_66>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_66> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_66/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where a supervisory authority has taken a measure pursuant to paragraph 1 and considers that final measures need urgently be adopted, it may request an urgent opinion or an urgent binding decision from the Board, giving reasons for requesting such opinion or decision."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 66, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 66 (Urgency procedure), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_66>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_66> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_66/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Any supervisory authority may request an urgent opinion or an urgent binding decision, as the case may be, from the Board where a competent supervisory authority has not taken an appropriate measure in a situation where there is an urgent need to act, in order to protect the rights and freedoms of data subjects, giving reasons for requesting such opinion or decision, including for the urgent need to act."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 66, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 66 (Urgency procedure), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_66>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_66> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_66/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "By derogation from Article 64(3) and Article 65(2), an urgent opinion or an urgent binding decision referred to in paragraphs 2 and 3 of this Article shall be adopted within two weeks by simple majority of the members of the Board."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 66, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 66 (Urgency procedure), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_66>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_66> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_67/Point_text_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Commission may adopt implementing acts of general scope in order to specify the arrangements for the exchange of information by electronic means between supervisory authorities, and between supervisory authorities and the Board, in particular the standardised format referred to in Article 64."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 67, point text_1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 67 (Exchange of information), point text_1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_67>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_67> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_67/Point_text_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Those implementing acts shall be adopted in accordance with the examination procedure referred to in Article 93(2)."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 67, point text_2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 67 (Exchange of information), point text_2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_67>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_67> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_68/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The European Data Protection Board (the ‘Board’) is hereby established as a body of the Union and shall have legal personality."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 68, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 68 (European Data Protection Board), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_68>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_68> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_68/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Board shall be represented by its Chair."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 68, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 68 (European Data Protection Board), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_68>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_68> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_68/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Board shall be composed of the head of one supervisory authority of each Member State and of the European Data Protection Supervisor, or their respective representatives."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 68, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 68 (European Data Protection Board), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_68>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_68> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_68/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where in a Member State more than one supervisory authority is responsible for monitoring the application of the provisions pursuant to this Regulation, a joint representative shall be appointed in accordance with that Member State's law."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 68, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 68 (European Data Protection Board), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_68>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_68> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_68/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Commission shall have the right to participate in the activities and meetings of the Board without voting right. The Commission shall designate a representative. The Chair of the Board shall communicate to the Commission the activities of the Board."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 68, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 68 (European Data Protection Board), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_68>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_68> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_68/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "In the cases referred to in Article 65, the European Data Protection Supervisor shall have voting rights only on decisions which concern principles and rules applicable to the Union institutions, bodies, offices and agencies which correspond in substance to those of this Regulation."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 68, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 68 (European Data Protection Board), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_68>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_68> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_69/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Board shall act independently when performing its tasks or exercising its powers pursuant to Articles 70 and 71."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 69, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 69 (Independence), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_69>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_69> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_69/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Without prejudice to requests by the Commission referred to in point (b) of Article 70(1) and in Article 70(2), the Board shall, in the performance of its tasks or the exercise of its powers, neither seek nor take instructions from anybody."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 69, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 69 (Independence), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_69>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_69> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Board shall ensure the consistent application of this Regulation. To that end, the Board shall, on its own initiative or, where relevant, at the request of the Commission, in particular:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "monitor and ensure the correct application of this Regulation in the cases provided for in Articles 64 and 65 without prejudice to the tasks of national supervisory authorities;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "advise the Commission on any issue related to the protection of personal data in the Union, including on any proposed amendment of this Regulation;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "advise the Commission on the format and procedures for the exchange of information between controllers, processors and supervisory authorities for binding corporate rules;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "issue guidelines, recommendations, and best practices on procedures for erasing links, copies or replications of personal data from publicly available communication services as referred to in Article 17(2);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "examine, on its own initiative, on request of one of its members or on request of the Commission, any question covering the application of this Regulation and issue guidelines, recommendations and best practices in order to encourage consistent application of this Regulation;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "issue guidelines, recommendations and best practices in accordance with point (e) of this paragraph for further specifying the criteria and conditions for decisions based on profiling pursuant to Article 22(2);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1g>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "issue guidelines, recommendations and best practices in accordance with point (e) of this paragraph for establishing the personal data breaches and determining the undue delay referred to in Article 33(1) and (2) and for the particular circumstances in which a controller or a processor is required to notify the personal data breach;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1g"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1g"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1h>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "issue guidelines, recommendations and best practices in accordance with point (e) of this paragraph as to the circumstances in which a personal data breach is likely to result in a high risk to the rights and freedoms of the natural persons referred to in Article 34(1)."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1h"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1h"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1i>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "issue guidelines, recommendations and best practices in accordance with point (e) of this paragraph for the purpose of further specifying the criteria and requirements for personal data transfers based on binding corporate rules adhered to by controllers and binding corporate rules adhered to by processors and on further necessary requirements to ensure the protection of personal data of the data subjects concerned referred to in Article 47;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1i"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1i"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1j>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "issue guidelines, recommendations and best practices in accordance with point (e) of this paragraph for the purpose of further specifying the criteria and requirements for the personal data transfers on the basis of Article 49(1);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1j"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1j"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1k>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "draw up guidelines for supervisory authorities concerning the application of measures referred to in Article 58(1), (2) and (3) and the setting of administrative fines pursuant to Article 83;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1k"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1k"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1l>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "review the practical application of the guidelines, recommendations and best practices referred to in points (e) and (f);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1l"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1l"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1m>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "issue guidelines, recommendations and best practices in accordance with point (e) of this paragraph for establishing common procedures for reporting by natural persons of infringements of this Regulation pursuant to Article 54(2);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1m"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1m"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1n>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "encourage the drawing-up of codes of conduct and the establishment of data protection certification mechanisms and data protection seals and marks pursuant to Articles 40 and 42;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1n"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1n"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
