<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1r>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "provide the Commission with an opinion on the icons referred to in Article 12(7);"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1r"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1r"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1s>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "provide the Commission with an opinion for the assessment of the adequacy of the level of protection in a third country or international organisation, including for the assessment whether a third country, a territory or one or more specified sectors within that third country, or an international organisation no longer ensures an adequate level of protection. To that end, the Commission shall provide the Board with all necessary documentation, including correspondence with the government of the third country, with regard to that third country, territory or specified sector, or with the international organisation."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1s"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1s"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1t>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "issue opinions on draft decisions of supervisory authorities pursuant to the consistency mechanism referred to in Article 64(1), on matters submitted pursuant to Article 64(2) and to issue binding decisions pursuant to Article 65, including in cases referred to in Article 66;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1t"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1t"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1u>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "promote the cooperation and the effective bilateral and multilateral exchange of information and best practices between the supervisory authorities;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1u"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1u"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1v>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "promote common training programmes and facilitate personnel exchanges between the supervisory authorities and, where appropriate, with the supervisory authorities of third countries or with international organisations;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1v"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1v"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1w>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "promote the exchange of knowledge and documentation on data protection legislation and practice with data protection supervisory authorities worldwide."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1w"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1w"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1x>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "issue opinions on codes of conduct drawn up at Union level pursuant to Article 40(9); and"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1x"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1x"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_1y>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "maintain a publicly accessible electronic register of decisions taken by supervisory authorities and courts on issues handled in the consistency mechanism."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 1y"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 1y"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where the Commission requests advice from the Board, it may indicate a time limit, taking into account the urgency of the matter."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Board shall forward its opinions, guidelines, recommendations, and best practices to the Commission and to the committee referred to in Article 93 and make them public."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Board shall, where appropriate, consult interested parties and give them the opportunity to comment within a reasonable period. The Board shall, without prejudice to Article 76, make the results of the consultation procedure publicly available."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 70, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 70 (Tasks of the Board), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_70>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_70> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_71/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Board shall draw up an annual report regarding the protection of natural persons with regard to processing in the Union and, where relevant, in third countries and international organisations. The report shall be made public and be transmitted to the European Parliament, to the Council and to the Commission."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 71, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 71 (Reports), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_71>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_71> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_71/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The annual report shall include a review of the practical application of the guidelines, recommendations and best practices referred to in point (l) of Article 70(1) as well as of the binding decisions referred to in Article 65."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 71, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 71 (Reports), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_71>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_71> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_72/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Board shall take decisions by a simple majority of its members, unless otherwise provided for in this Regulation."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 72, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 72 (Procedure), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_72>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_72> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_72/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Board shall adopt its own rules of procedure by a two-thirds majority of its members and organise its own operational arrangements."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 72, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 72 (Procedure), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_72>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_72> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_73/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Board shall elect a chair and two deputy chairs from amongst its members by simple majority."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 73, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 73 (Chair), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_73>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_73> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_73/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The term of office of the Chair and of the deputy chairs shall be five years and be renewable once."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 73, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 73 (Chair), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_73>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_73> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_74/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Chair shall have the following tasks:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 74, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 74 (Tasks of the Chair), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_74>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_74> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_74/Point_1a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to convene the meetings of the Board and prepare its agenda;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 74, point 1a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 74 (Tasks of the Chair), point 1a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_74>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_74> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_74/Point_1b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to notify decisions adopted by the Board pursuant to Article 65 to the lead supervisory authority and the supervisory authorities concerned;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 74, point 1b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 74 (Tasks of the Chair), point 1b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_74>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_74> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_74/Point_1c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "to ensure the timely performance of the tasks of the Board, in particular in relation to the consistency mechanism referred to in Article 63."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 74, point 1c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 74 (Tasks of the Chair), point 1c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_74>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_74> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_74/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Board shall lay down the allocation of tasks between the Chair and the deputy chairs in its rules of procedure."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 74, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 74 (Tasks of the Chair), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_74>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_74> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Board shall have a secretariat, which shall be provided by the European Data Protection Supervisor."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 75, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 75 (Secretariat), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_75> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The secretariat shall perform its tasks exclusively under the instructions of the Chair of the Board."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 75, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 75 (Secretariat), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_75> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The staff of the European Data Protection Supervisor involved in carrying out the tasks conferred on the Board by this Regulation shall be subject to separate reporting lines from the staff involved in carrying out tasks conferred on the European Data Protection Supervisor."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 75, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 75 (Secretariat), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_75> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where appropriate, the Board and the European Data Protection Supervisor shall establish and publish a Memorandum of Understanding implementing this Article, determining the terms of their cooperation, and applicable to the staff of the European Data Protection Supervisor involved in carrying out the tasks conferred on the Board by this Regulation."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 75, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 75 (Secretariat), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_75> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The secretariat shall provide analytical, administrative and logistical support to the Board."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 75, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 75 (Secretariat), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_75> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The secretariat shall be responsible in particular for:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 75, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 75 (Secretariat), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_75> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75/Point_6a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the day-to-day business of the Board;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 75, point 6a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 75 (Secretariat), point 6a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_75> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75/Point_6b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "communication between the members of the Board, its Chair and the Commission;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 75, point 6b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 75 (Secretariat), point 6b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_75> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75/Point_6c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "communication with other institutions and the public;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 75, point 6c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 75 (Secretariat), point 6c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_75> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75/Point_6d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the use of electronic means for the internal and external communication;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 75, point 6d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 75 (Secretariat), point 6d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_75> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75/Point_6e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the translation of relevant information;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 75, point 6e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 75 (Secretariat), point 6e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_75> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75/Point_6f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the preparation and follow-up of the meetings of the Board;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 75, point 6f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 75 (Secretariat), point 6f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_75> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75/Point_6g>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the preparation, drafting and publication of opinions, decisions on the settlement of disputes between supervisory authorities and other texts adopted by the Board."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 75, point 6g"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 75 (Secretariat), point 6g"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_75>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_75> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_76/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The discussions of the Board shall be confidential where the Board deems it necessary, as provided for in its rules of procedure."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 76, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 76 (Confidentiality), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_76>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_76> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_76/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Access to documents submitted to members of the Board, experts and representatives of third parties shall be governed by Regulation (EC) No 1049/2001 of the European Parliament and of the Council (21)."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VII, article 76, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VII (Cooperation and consistency), article 76 (Confidentiality), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VII/Article_76>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_vii_article_76> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_77/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Without prejudice to any other administrative or judicial remedy, every data subject shall have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority, in particular in the Member State of his or her habitual residence, place of work or place of the alleged infringement if the data subject considers that the processing of personal data relating to him or her infringes this Regulation."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 77, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 77 (Right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_77>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_77> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_77/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The supervisory authority with which the complaint has been lodged shall inform the complainant on the progress and the outcome of the complaint including the possibility of a judicial remedy pursuant to Article 78."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 77, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 77 (Right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_77>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_77> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_78/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Without prejudice to any other administrative or non-judicial remedy, each natural or legal person shall have the right to an effective judicial remedy against a legally binding decision of a supervisory authority concerning them."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 78, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 78 (Right to an effective judicial remedy against a supervisory authority), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_78>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_78> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_78/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Without prejudice to any other administrative or non-judicial remedy, each data subject shall have the right to a an effective judicial remedy where the supervisory authority which is competent pursuant to Articles 55 and 56 does not handle a complaint or does not inform the data subject within three months on the progress or outcome of the complaint lodged pursuant to Article 77."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 78, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 78 (Right to an effective judicial remedy against a supervisory authority), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_78>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_78> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_78/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Proceedings against a supervisory authority shall be brought before the courts of the Member State where the supervisory authority is established."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 78, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 78 (Right to an effective judicial remedy against a supervisory authority), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_78>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_78> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_78/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where proceedings are brought against a decision of a supervisory authority which was preceded by an opinion or a decision of the Board in the consistency mechanism, the supervisory authority shall forward that opinion or decision to the court."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 78, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 78 (Right to an effective judicial remedy against a supervisory authority), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_78>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_78> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_79/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Without prejudice to any available administrative or non-judicial remedy, including the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority pursuant to Article 77, each data subject shall have the right to an effective judicial remedy where he or she considers that his or her rights under this Regulation have been infringed as a result of the processing of his or her personal data in non-compliance with this Regulation."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 79, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 79 (Right to an effective judicial remedy against a controller or processor), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_79>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_79> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_79/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Proceedings against a controller or a processor shall be brought before the courts of the Member State where the controller or processor has an establishment. Alternatively, such proceedings may be brought before the courts of the Member State where the data subject has his or her habitual residence, unless the controller or processor is a public authority of a Member State acting in the exercise of its public powers."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 79, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 79 (Right to an effective judicial remedy against a controller or processor), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_79>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_79> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_80/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The data subject shall have the right to mandate a not-for-profit body, organisation or association which has been properly constituted in accordance with the law of a Member State, has statutory objectives which are in the public interest, and is active in the field of the protection of data subjects' rights and freedoms with regard to the protection of their personal data to lodge the complaint on his or her behalf, to exercise the rights referred to in Articles 77, 78 and 79 on his or her behalf, and to exercise the right to receive compensation referred to in Article 82 on his or her behalf where provided for by Member State law."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 80, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 80 (Representation of data subjects), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_80>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_80> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_80/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Member States may provide that any body, organisation or association referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article, independently of a data subject's mandate, has the right to lodge, in that Member State, a complaint with the supervisory authority which is competent pursuant to Article 77 and to exercise the rights referred to in Articles 78 and 79 if it considers that the rights of a data subject under this Regulation have been infringed as a result of the processing."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 80, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 80 (Representation of data subjects), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_80>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_80> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_81/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where a competent court of a Member State has information on proceedings, concerning the same subject matter as regards processing by the same controller or processor, that are pending in a court in another Member State, it shall contact that court in the other Member State to confirm the existence of such proceedings."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 81, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 81 (Suspension of proceedings), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_81>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_81> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_81/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where proceedings concerning the same subject matter as regards processing of the same controller or processor are pending in a court in another Member State, any competent court other than the court first seized may suspend its proceedings."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 81, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 81 (Suspension of proceedings), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_81>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_81> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_81/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where those proceedings are pending at first instance, any court other than the court first seized may also, on the application of one of the parties, decline jurisdiction if the court first seized has jurisdiction over the actions in question and its law permits the consolidation thereof."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 81, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 81 (Suspension of proceedings), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_81>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_81> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_82/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Any person who has suffered material or non-material damage as a result of an infringement of this Regulation shall have the right to receive compensation from the controller or processor for the damage suffered."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 82, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 82 (Right to compensation and liability), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_82>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_82> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_82/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Any controller involved in processing shall be liable for the damage caused by processing which infringes this Regulation. A processor shall be liable for the damage caused by processing only where it has not complied with obligations of this Regulation specifically directed to processors or where it has acted outside or contrary to lawful instructions of the controller."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 82, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 82 (Right to compensation and liability), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_82>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_82> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_82/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "A controller or processor shall be exempt from liability under paragraph 2 if it proves that it is not in any way responsible for the event giving rise to the damage."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 82, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 82 (Right to compensation and liability), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_82>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_82> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_82/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where more than one controller or processor, or both a controller and a processor, are involved in the same processing and where they are, under paragraphs 2 and 3, responsible for any damage caused by processing, each controller or processor shall be held liable for the entire damage in order to ensure effective compensation of the data subject."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 82, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 82 (Right to compensation and liability), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_82>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_82> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_82/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where a controller or processor has, in accordance with paragraph 4, paid full compensation for the damage suffered, that controller or processor shall be entitled to claim back from the other controllers or processors involved in the same processing that part of the compensation corresponding to their part of responsibility for the damage, in accordance with the conditions set out in paragraph 2."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 82, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 82 (Right to compensation and liability), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_82>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_82> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_82/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Court proceedings for exercising the right to receive compensation shall be brought before the courts competent under the law of the Member State referred to in Article 79(2)."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 82, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 82 (Right to compensation and liability), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_82>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_82> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each supervisory authority shall ensure that the imposition of administrative fines pursuant to this Article in respect of infringements of this Regulation referred to in paragraphs 4, 5 and 6 shall in each individual case be effective, proportionate and dissuasive."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Administrative fines shall, depending on the circumstances of each individual case, be imposed in addition to, or instead of, measures referred to in points (a) to (h) and (j) of Article 58(2). When deciding whether to impose an administrative fine and deciding on the amount of the administrative fine in each individual case due regard shall be given to the following:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_2a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the nature, gravity and duration of the infringement taking into account the nature scope or purpose of the processing concerned as well as the number of data subjects affected and the level of damage suffered by them;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 2a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 2a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_2b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the intentional or negligent character of the infringement;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 2b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 2b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_2c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "any action taken by the controller or processor to mitigate the damage suffered by data subjects;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 2c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 2c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_2d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the degree of responsibility of the controller or processor taking into account technical and organisational measures implemented by them pursuant to Articles 25 and 32;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 2d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 2d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_2e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "any relevant previous infringements by the controller or processor;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 2e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 2e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_2f>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the degree of cooperation with the supervisory authority, in order to remedy the infringement and mitigate the possible adverse effects of the infringement;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 2f"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 2f"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_2g>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the categories of personal data affected by the infringement;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 2g"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 2g"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_2h>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the manner in which the infringement became known to the supervisory authority, in particular whether, and if so to what extent, the controller or processor notified the infringement;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 2h"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 2h"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_2i>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "where measures referred to in Article 58(2) have previously been ordered against the controller or processor concerned with regard to the same subject-matter, compliance with those measures;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 2i"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 2i"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_2j>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "adherence to approved codes of conduct pursuant to Article 40 or approved certification mechanisms pursuant to Article 42; and"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 2j"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 2j"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_2k>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "any other aggravating or mitigating factor applicable to the circumstances of the case, such as financial benefits gained, or losses avoided, directly or indirectly, from the infringement."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 2k"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 2k"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "If a controller or processor intentionally or negligently, for the same or linked processing operations, infringes several provisions of this Regulation, the total amount of the administrative fine shall not exceed the amount specified for the gravest infringement."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Infringements of the following provisions shall, in accordance with paragraph 2, be subject to administrative fines up to 10 000 000 EUR, or in the case of an undertaking, up to 2 % of the total worldwide annual turnover of the preceding financial year, whichever is higher:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_4a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the obligations of the controller and the processor pursuant to Articles 8, 11, 25 to 39 and 42 and 43;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 4a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 4a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_4b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the obligations of the certification body pursuant to Articles 42 and 43;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 4b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 4b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_4c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the obligations of the monitoring body pursuant to Article 41(4)."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 4c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 4c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Infringements of the following provisions shall, in accordance with paragraph 2, be subject to administrative fines up to 20 000 000 EUR, or in the case of an undertaking, up to 4 % of the total worldwide annual turnover of the preceding financial year, whichever is higher:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_5a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the basic principles for processing, including conditions for consent, pursuant to Articles 5, 6, 7 and 9;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 5a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 5a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_5b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the data subjects' rights pursuant to Articles 12 to 22;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 5b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 5b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_5c>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "the transfers of personal data to a recipient in a third country or an international organisation pursuant to Articles 44 to 49;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 5c"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 5c"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_5d>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "any obligations pursuant to Member State law adopted under Chapter IX;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 5d"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 5d"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_5e>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "non-compliance with an order or a temporary or definitive limitation on processing or the suspension of data flows by the supervisory authority pursuant to Article 58(2) or failure to provide access in violation of Article 58(1)."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 5e"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 5e"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_6>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Non-compliance with an order by the supervisory authority as referred to in Article 58(2) shall, in accordance with paragraph 2 of this Article, be subject to administrative fines up to 20 000 000 EUR, or in the case of an undertaking, up to 4 % of the total worldwide annual turnover of the preceding financial year, whichever is higher."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 6"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 6"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_7>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Without prejudice to the corrective powers of supervisory authorities pursuant to Article 58(2), each Member State may lay down the rules on whether and to what extent administrative fines may be imposed on public authorities and bodies established in that Member State."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 7"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 7"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_8>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The exercise by the supervisory authority of its powers under this Article shall be subject to appropriate procedural safeguards in accordance with Union and Member State law, including effective judicial remedy and due process."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 8"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 8"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83/Point_9>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where the legal system of the Member State does not provide for administrative fines, this Article may be applied in such a manner that the fine is initiated by the competent supervisory authority and imposed by competent national courts, while ensuring that those legal remedies are effective and have an equivalent effect to the administrative fines imposed by supervisory authorities. In any event, the fines imposed shall be effective, proportionate and dissuasive. Those Member States shall notify to the Commission the provisions of their laws which they adopt pursuant to this paragraph by 25 May 2018 and, without delay, any subsequent amendment law or amendment affecting them."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 83, point 9"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 83 (General conditions for imposing administrative fines), point 9"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_83>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_83> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_84/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Member States shall lay down the rules on other penalties applicable to infringements of this Regulation in particular for infringements which are not subject to administrative fines pursuant to Article 83, and shall take all measures necessary to ensure that they are implemented. Such penalties shall be effective, proportionate and dissuasive."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 84, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 84 (Penalties), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_84>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_84> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_84/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each Member State shall notify to the Commission the provisions of its law which it adopts pursuant to paragraph 1, by 25 May 2018 and, without delay, any subsequent amendment affecting them."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter VIII, article 84, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter VIII (Remedies, liability and penalties), article 84 (Penalties), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_VIII/Article_84>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_viii_article_84> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_85/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Member States shall by law reconcile the right to the protection of personal data pursuant to this Regulation with the right to freedom of expression and information, including processing for journalistic purposes and the purposes of academic, artistic or literary expression."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IX, article 85, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IX (Provisions relating to specific processing situations), article 85 (Processing and freedom of expression and information), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_85>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ix_article_85> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_85/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "For processing carried out for journalistic purposes or the purpose of academic artistic or literary expression, Member States shall provide for exemptions or derogations from Chapter II (principles), Chapter III (rights of the data subject), Chapter IV (controller and processor), Chapter V (transfer of personal data to third countries or international organisations), Chapter VI (independent supervisory authorities), Chapter VII (cooperation and consistency) and Chapter IX (specific data processing situations) if they are necessary to reconcile the right to the protection of personal data with the freedom of expression and information."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IX, article 85, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IX (Provisions relating to specific processing situations), article 85 (Processing and freedom of expression and information), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_85>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ix_article_85> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_85/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each Member State shall notify to the Commission the provisions of its law which it has adopted pursuant to paragraph 2 and, without delay, any subsequent amendment law or amendment affecting them."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IX, article 85, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IX (Provisions relating to specific processing situations), article 85 (Processing and freedom of expression and information), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_85>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ix_article_85> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_86/Point_text_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Personal data in official documents held by a public authority or a public body or a private body for the performance of a task carried out in the public interest may be disclosed by the authority or body in accordance with Union or Member State law to which the public authority or body is subject in order to reconcile public access to official documents with the right to the protection of personal data pursuant to this Regulation."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IX, article 86, point text_1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IX (Provisions relating to specific processing situations), article 86 (Processing and public access to official documents), point text_1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_86>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ix_article_86> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_87/Point_text_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Member States may further determine the specific conditions for the processing of a national identification number or any other identifier of general application. In that case the national identification number or any other identifier of general application shall be used only under appropriate safeguards for the rights and freedoms of the data subject pursuant to this Regulation."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IX, article 87, point text_1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IX (Provisions relating to specific processing situations), article 87 (Processing of the national identification number), point text_1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_87>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ix_article_87> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_88/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Member States may, by law or by collective agreements, provide for more specific rules to ensure the protection of the rights and freedoms in respect of the processing of employees' personal data in the employment context, in particular for the purposes of the recruitment, the performance of the contract of employment, including discharge of obligations laid down by law or by collective agreements, management, planning and organisation of work, equality and diversity in the workplace, health and safety at work, protection of employer's or customer's property and for the purposes of the exercise and enjoyment, on an individual or collective basis, of rights and benefits related to employment, and for the purpose of the termination of the employment relationship."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IX, article 88, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IX (Provisions relating to specific processing situations), article 88 (Processing in the context of employment), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_88>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ix_article_88> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_88/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Those rules shall include suitable and specific measures to safeguard the data subject's human dignity, legitimate interests and fundamental rights, with particular regard to the transparency of processing, the transfer of personal data within a group of undertakings, or a group of enterprises engaged in a joint economic activity and monitoring systems at the work place."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IX, article 88, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IX (Provisions relating to specific processing situations), article 88 (Processing in the context of employment), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_88>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ix_article_88> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_88/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each Member State shall notify to the Commission those provisions of its law which it adopts pursuant to paragraph 1, by 25 May 2018 and, without delay, any subsequent amendment affecting them."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IX, article 88, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IX (Provisions relating to specific processing situations), article 88 (Processing in the context of employment), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_88>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ix_article_88> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_89/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Processing for archiving purposes in the public interest, scientific or historical research purposes or statistical purposes, shall be subject to appropriate safeguards, in accordance with this Regulation, for the rights and freedoms of the data subject. Those safeguards shall ensure that technical and organisational measures are in place in particular in order to ensure respect for the principle of data minimisation. Those measures may include pseudonymisation provided that those purposes can be fulfilled in that manner. Where those purposes can be fulfilled by further processing which does not permit or no longer permits the identification of data subjects, those purposes shall be fulfilled in that manner."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IX, article 89, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IX (Provisions relating to specific processing situations), article 89 (Safeguards and derogations relating to processing for archiving purposes in the public interest, scientific or historical research purposes or statistical purposes), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_89>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ix_article_89> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_89/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where personal data are processed for scientific or historical research purposes or statistical purposes, Union or Member State law may provide for derogations from the rights referred to in Articles 15, 16, 18 and 21 subject to the conditions and safeguards referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article in so far as such rights are likely to render impossible or seriously impair the achievement of the specific purposes, and such derogations are necessary for the fulfilment of those purposes."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IX, article 89, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IX (Provisions relating to specific processing situations), article 89 (Safeguards and derogations relating to processing for archiving purposes in the public interest, scientific or historical research purposes or statistical purposes), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_89>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ix_article_89> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_89/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where personal data are processed for archiving purposes in the public interest, Union or Member State law may provide for derogations from the rights referred to in Articles 15, 16, 18, 19, 20 and 21 subject to the conditions and safeguards referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article in so far as such rights are likely to render impossible or seriously impair the achievement of the specific purposes, and such derogations are necessary for the fulfilment of those purposes."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IX, article 89, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IX (Provisions relating to specific processing situations), article 89 (Safeguards and derogations relating to processing for archiving purposes in the public interest, scientific or historical research purposes or statistical purposes), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_89>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ix_article_89> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_89/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where processing referred to in paragraphs 2 and 3 serves at the same time another purpose, the derogations shall apply only to processing for the purposes referred to in those paragraphs."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IX, article 89, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IX (Provisions relating to specific processing situations), article 89 (Safeguards and derogations relating to processing for archiving purposes in the public interest, scientific or historical research purposes or statistical purposes), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_89>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ix_article_89> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_90/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Member States may adopt specific rules to set out the powers of the supervisory authorities laid down in points (e) and (f) of Article 58(1) in relation to controllers or processors that are subject, under Union or Member State law or rules established by national competent bodies, to an obligation of professional secrecy or other equivalent obligations of secrecy where this is necessary and proportionate to reconcile the right of the protection of personal data with the obligation of secrecy. Those rules shall apply only with regard to personal data which the controller or processor has received as a result of or has obtained in an activity covered by that obligation of secrecy."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IX, article 90, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IX (Provisions relating to specific processing situations), article 90 (Obligations of secrecy), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_90>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ix_article_90> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_90/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Each Member State shall notify to the Commission the rules adopted pursuant to paragraph 1, by 25 May 2018 and, without delay, any subsequent amendment affecting them."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IX, article 90, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IX (Provisions relating to specific processing situations), article 90 (Obligations of secrecy), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_90>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ix_article_90> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_91/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where in a Member State, churches and religious associations or communities apply, at the time of entry into force of this Regulation, comprehensive rules relating to the protection of natural persons with regard to processing, such rules may continue to apply, provided that they are brought into line with this Regulation."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IX, article 91, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IX (Provisions relating to specific processing situations), article 91 (Existing data protection rules of churches and religious associations), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_91>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ix_article_91> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_91/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Churches and religious associations which apply comprehensive rules in accordance with paragraph 1 of this Article shall be subject to the supervision of an independent supervisory authority, which may be specific, provided that it fulfils the conditions laid down in Chapter VI of this Regulation."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter IX, article 91, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter IX (Provisions relating to specific processing situations), article 91 (Existing data protection rules of churches and religious associations), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_IX/Article_91>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_ix_article_91> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_X/Article_92/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The power to adopt delegated acts is conferred on the Commission subject to the conditions laid down in this Article."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter X, article 92, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter X (Delegated acts and implementing acts), article 92 (Exercise of the delegation), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_X/Article_92>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_x_article_92> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_X/Article_92/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The delegation of power referred to in Article 12(8) and Article 43(8) shall be conferred on the Commission for an indeterminate period of time from 24 May 2016."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter X, article 92, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter X (Delegated acts and implementing acts), article 92 (Exercise of the delegation), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_X/Article_92>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_x_article_92> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_X/Article_92/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The delegation of power referred to in Article 12(8) and Article 43(8) may be revoked at any time by the European Parliament or by the Council. A decision of revocation shall put an end to the delegation of power specified in that decision. It shall take effect the day following that of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Union or at a later date specified therein. It shall not affect the validity of any delegated acts already in force."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter X, article 92, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter X (Delegated acts and implementing acts), article 92 (Exercise of the delegation), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_X/Article_92>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_x_article_92> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_X/Article_92/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "As soon as it adopts a delegated act, the Commission shall notify it simultaneously to the European Parliament and to the Council."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter X, article 92, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter X (Delegated acts and implementing acts), article 92 (Exercise of the delegation), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_X/Article_92>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_x_article_92> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_X/Article_92/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "A delegated act adopted pursuant to Article 12(8) and Article 43(8) shall enter into force only if no objection has been expressed by either the European Parliament or the Council within a period of three months of notification of that act to the European Parliament and the Council or if, before the expiry of that period, the European Parliament and the Council have both informed the Commission that they will not object. That period shall be extended by three months at the initiative of the European Parliament or of the Council."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter X, article 92, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter X (Delegated acts and implementing acts), article 92 (Exercise of the delegation), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_X/Article_92>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_x_article_92> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_X/Article_93/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Commission shall be assisted by a committee. That committee shall be a committee within the meaning of Regulation (EU) No 182/2011."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter X, article 93, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter X (Delegated acts and implementing acts), article 93 (Committee procedure), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_X/Article_93>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_x_article_93> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_X/Article_93/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where reference is made to this paragraph, Article 5 of Regulation (EU) No 182/2011 shall apply."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter X, article 93, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter X (Delegated acts and implementing acts), article 93 (Committee procedure), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_X/Article_93>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_x_article_93> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_X/Article_93/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Where reference is made to this paragraph, Article 8 of Regulation (EU) No 182/2011, in conjunction with Article 5 thereof, shall apply."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter X, article 93, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter X (Delegated acts and implementing acts), article 93 (Committee procedure), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_X/Article_93>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_x_article_93> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_94/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "Directive 95/46/EC is repealed with effect from 25 May 2018."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter XI, article 94, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter XI (Final provisions), article 94 (Repeal of Directive 95/46/EC), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_94>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_xi_article_94> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_94/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "References to the repealed Directive shall be construed as references to this Regulation. References to the Working Party on the Protection of Individuals with regard to the Processing of Personal Data established by Article 29 of Directive 95/46/EC shall be construed as references to the European Data Protection Board established by this Regulation."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter XI, article 94, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter XI (Final provisions), article 94 (Repeal of Directive 95/46/EC), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_94>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_xi_article_94> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_95/Point_text_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "This Regulation shall not impose additional obligations on natural or legal persons in relation to processing in connection with the provision of publicly available electronic communications services in public communication networks in the Union in relation to matters for which they are subject to specific obligations with the same objective set out in Directive 2002/58/EC."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter XI, article 95, point text_1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter XI (Final provisions), article 95 (Relationship with Directive 2002/58/EC), point text_1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_95>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_xi_article_95> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_96/Point_text_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "International agreements involving the transfer of personal data to third countries or international organisations which were concluded by Member States prior to 24 May 2016, and which comply with Union law as applicable prior to that date, shall remain in force until amended, replaced or revoked."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter XI, article 96, point text_1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter XI (Final provisions), article 96 (Relationship with previously concluded Agreements), point text_1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_96>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_xi_article_96> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_97/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "By 25 May 2020 and every four years thereafter, the Commission shall submit a report on the evaluation and review of this Regulation to the European Parliament and to the Council. The reports shall be made public."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter XI, article 97, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter XI (Final provisions), article 97 (Commission reports), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_97>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_xi_article_97> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_97/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "In the context of the evaluations and reviews referred to in paragraph 1, the Commission shall examine, in particular, the application and functioning of:"@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter XI, article 97, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter XI (Final provisions), article 97 (Commission reports), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_97>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_xi_article_97> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_97/Point_2a>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "Chapter V on the transfer of personal data to third countries or international organisations with particular regard to decisions adopted pursuant to Article 45(3) of this Regulation and decisions adopted on the basis of Article 25(6) of Directive 95/46/EC;"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter XI, article 97, point 2a"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter XI (Final provisions), article 97 (Commission reports), point 2a"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_97>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_xi_article_97> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_97/Point_2b>
                    a v:Point ;            
                    v:fullText "Chapter VII on cooperation and consistency."@en ;
                    v:breadcrumb        "chapter XI, article 97, point 2b"@en ;
                    v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter XI (Final provisions), article 97 (Commission reports), point 2b"@en ;
                    v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_97>;  
                    v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_xi_article_97> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_97/Point_3>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "For the purpose of paragraph 1, the Commission may request information from Member States and supervisory authorities."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter XI, article 97, point 3"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter XI (Final provisions), article 97 (Commission reports), point 3"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_97>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_xi_article_97> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_97/Point_4>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "In carrying out the evaluations and reviews referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2, the Commission shall take into account the positions and findings of the European Parliament, of the Council, and of other relevant bodies or sources."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter XI, article 97, point 4"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter XI (Final provisions), article 97 (Commission reports), point 4"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_97>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_xi_article_97> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_97/Point_5>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Commission shall, if necessary, submit appropriate proposals to amend this Regulation, in particular taking into account of developments in information technology and in the light of the state of progress in the information society."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter XI, article 97, point 5"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter XI (Final provisions), article 97 (Commission reports), point 5"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_97>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_xi_article_97> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_98/Point_text_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "The Commission shall, if appropriate, submit legislative proposals with a view to amending other Union legal acts on the protection of personal data, in order to ensure uniform and consistent protection of natural persons with regard to processing. This shall in particular concern the rules relating to the protection of natural persons with regard to processing by Union institutions, bodies, offices and agencies and on the free movement of such data."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter XI, article 98, point text_1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter XI (Final provisions), article 98 (Review of other Union legal acts on data protection), point text_1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_98>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_xi_article_98> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_99/Point_1>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "This Regulation shall enter into force on the twentieth day following that of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Union."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter XI, article 99, point 1"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter XI (Final provisions), article 99 (Entry into force and application), point 1"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_99>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_xi_article_99> .
<https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_99/Point_2>
                a v:Point ;            
                v:fullText "It shall apply from 25 May 2018."@en ;
                v:breadcrumb        "chapter XI, article 99, point 2"@en ;
                v:breadcrumbLabel   "chapter XI (Final provisions), article 99 (Entry into force and application), point 2"@en ;
                v:isPartOfArticle <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/Chapter_XI/Article_99>;  
                v:refersTo <https://omc.co/5511993891773/7492/chapter_xi_article_99> .
